En nummerväst använd och signerad av alpina skidåkaren Anja Pärson.  Västen användes under världsmästerskapen i alpin skidsport 2005 i Bormio, Italien.

Anja Pärson (1981-) är en svensk alpin skidåkare. Efter bronsmedaljen på lagtävlingen under VM 2011 i Garmisch-Partenkirchen blev Pärson historisk och bäst genom tiderna i modern tid med tretton VM-medaljer. När Pärson avslutade sin skidkarriär 2012 hade hon bland annat 42 världscupsegrar, ett OS-guld, sju VM-guld och totalt 19 mästerskapsmedaljer. Pärson tävlade för IK Fjällvinden i Tärnaby.

http://data.europeana.eu/item/847/RIM_it.description:
Ski suit used by Anja Pärson during the early 2000s.

Anja Pärson (1981-) is a Swedish alpine skier. After the bronze medal at the team competition during the World Cup 2011 in Garmisch-Partenkirchen, Pärson became historic and best of all time in modern times with thirteen World Cup medals. When Pärson finished his skiing career in 2012, she had among others 42 World Cup victories, one Olympic gold, seven World Cup gold and a total of 19 championship medals. Pärson competed for IK The Mountain Wind in Tärnaby.

The International Archery Association’s Merit Medal Marked;

"MERITE INTERNATIONAL
FEDERATION INTERNATIONALE DE TIR A L “ARC”

The World Archery Federation (WAF) is the International Archery Federation. It was formed in 1931 under the name Fédération Internationale de Tir à l 'Arc (1931-2011). The Association arranges the world championships in archery.

Archery is a sport branch, which occurs among other things in the Olympic Games. Archery was a popular sport in the Middle Ages. In Sweden, the first archery club, Stockholm’s archery club, was formed in 1928. The Swedish Archery Association was established in 1940.

http://data.europeana.eu/item/2021648/re.description: Een bronzen plaquette met afbeelding van drie dansende dames met opschrift: "Olympisch - Mien v.d. Berg - Kampioene". Jacomina Elisabeth Sophia (Mien) van den Berg (Den Haag, 28 december 1909 - aldaar, 14 november 1996) was een Nederlandse gymnaste. Zij maakte deel uit van de turnploeg die goud won tijdens de Olympische Zomerspelen 1928 van Amsterdam. De dames van deze ploeg waren de eerste Nederlandse vrouwelijke Olympische kampioenen. Hun coach was Gerrit Kleerekoper.

http://data.europeana.eu/item/2021648/re.description: Een zilveren medaille met opschrift "D.W.S. 1e prijs 1948". Jacomina Elisabeth Sophia (Mien) van den Berg (Den Haag, 28 december 1909 - aldaar, 14 november 1996) was een Nederlandse gymnasiaste. Zij maakte deel uit van de turnploeg die goud won tijdens de Olympische Zomerspelen 1928 van Amsterdam. De dames van deze ploeg waren de eerste Nederlandse vrouwelijke Olympische kampioenen. Hun coach was Gerrit Kleerekoper.

http://data.europeana.eu/item/951/Cultur.description: Insignă pentru ștafeta Tito, organizată în anul 1947. Pe avers, în centru, este reprezentat un atlet care aleargă, acesta fiind înconjurat de o cunună alcătuită din frunze de laur. Peste cunună, în partea superioară, sunt suprapuse șase stele, iar în partea inferioară este suprapusă o panglică pe care apare denumirea întrecerii sportive și anul organizării acesteia - TITOVA STAFETA 1947. Pe revers se regăsește negativul aversului. Bună. Stratul argintat este tocit în anumite zone, iar pe ambele părți sunt multiple zgârieturi și pete închise la culoare.

Lavan etupinnalla on puolivartalokuvana esitetty naishahmo, jolla on topatut vaatteet. Hahmo on kohollaan alustasta myös sen alle laitettujen pahvisten korokkeiden ansiosta. Naisen hiuslaitteessa on hopeanvärisiä paperikoristeita ja harteilla on violettikukkainen oksa. Lavan puunväriselle taustapuolelle on maalattu punainen kasviaihe. Mailan kädensija on päällystetty kullan ja mustan värisellä kankaalla. Mailan takaosaan on teipattu lappu, jossa lukee ” vanhanaikainen sulkapallomaila, nykyään käytetään koristeena”

http://data.europeana.eu/item/1190/INP_p.description: Bazinul cu apă minerală a fost construit încă din 1874, vreme la care era primul de acest fel din Europa și care și-a păstrat unicitatea prin calitatea apelor minerale naturale cu care este alimentat. Ștrandul, împreună cu toate atracțiile acestei stațiuni balneare de interes național, s-au aflat în ruine mai bine de 30 de ani, în pofida importanței lor turistice. Cu ajutorul unor fonduri europene, autoritățile locale au reușit să reabiliteze în ultimii ani vechile clădiri, să refacă aleile și să introducă un nou sistem de iluminat în parc. Acest proces de salvare și punere în valoare a patrimoniului imobil al orașului Buziaș ar urma să resusciteze potențialul turistic al acestuia. Mai multe informații despre această stațiune și situația ei actuală puteți afla accesând site-ul: https://observatornews.ro/exclusiv-observator/fosta-perla-balneara-a-tarii-o-ruina-intre-gunoaie-cum-arata-acum-statiunea-buzias-odinioara-admirata-de-imparatul-franz-joseph-508263.html
http://data.europeana.eu/item/1190/INP_p.title: Buziaș - Complex Parc; Ștrandul

http://data.europeana.eu/item/1190/INP_p.description: Parcul din Buziaș a fost construit în secolul al XIX-lea. Un punct de atracție din parc este colonada din lemn, o pergolă acoperită, unică în Europa pentru lungimea sa de 500 m, construită în stil turco-bizantin în anul 1875. Colonada înconjoară parcul, făcând legătura între Izvorul Josif, Hotelul Phoenix, bazarul, Izvorul Mihai și Cazino. Aerul puternic ionizat negativ, datorită emanațiilor de la sonde, explică efectul benefic al plimbărilor pe sub colonadă. Parcul este cunoscut și pentru pavilionul cu ape minerale cu efect curativ. Colonada avea rol de a-i proteja pe vizitatori de condiții meteo nefavorabile, permițând astfel o plimbare liniștită prin parc în orice condiții. Ștrandul, împreună cu toate atracțiile acestei stațiuni balneare de interes național, s-au aflat în ruine mai bine de 30 de ani, în pofida importanței lor turistice. Cu ajutorul unor fonduri europene, autoritățile locale au reușit să reabiliteze în ultimii ani vechile clădiri, să refacă aleile și să introducă un nou sistem de iluminat în parc. Acest proces de salvare și punere în valoare a patrimoniului imobil al orașului Buziaș ar urma să resusciteze potențialul turistic al acestuia. Mai multe informații despre această stațiune și situația ei actuală puteți afla accesând site-ul: https://observatornews.ro/exclusiv-observator/fosta-perla-balneara-a-tarii-o-ruina-intre-gunoaie-cum-arata-acum-statiunea-buzias-odinioara-admirata-de-imparatul-franz-joseph-508263.html
http://data.europeana.eu/item/1190/INP_p.title: Buziaș - Complex Parc; Ștrandul

http://data.europeana.eu/item/1190/INP_p.description: Arhitectura Complexului turistic si comercial Parc - este specifică anilor socialismului în România. Ștrandul făcea parte din amenajările acestei localități-stațiune cunoscută încă din perioada romană pentru bogatele izvoare cu minerale. Începând cu secolul al XIX-lea, aici se pun bazele realizării unei stațiuni de tratamente pentru diverse afecțiuni cardiovasculare, gastrice, reumatismale, infecțioase și respiratorii pentru care, apele minerale, cele sulfuroase și sărate și mofetele, precum și aerul bogat în ozon au fost și sunt folosite în operațiuni specifice tratamentelor balneare. Specificul curativ al stațiunii este cunoscut și extrem de apreciat și căutat și în prezent și exploatat cu succes în tratarea diverselor afecțiuni.

http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.description:
Ik speel al heel lang honkbal en softbal. Vroeger deed ik dat bij de Amsterdamse Maatschappij voor Jonge Mannen (AMVJ) in Amsterdam Zuid.

Een keer moesten we een uitwedstrijd spelen in Huizen in het Gooi en we waren te laat vertrokken. Een teamgenoot meende wel een binnenweg te weten zodat we alsnog op tijd bij de wedstrijd konden zijn. We reden dus dwars door het Gooi heen, langs alle dorpen. Ik zat zelf achter het stuur en toen we bij stoplichten aankwamen parkeerde ik even op de kruising om de weg te zoeken. 

Er stopte toen een Saab cabrio naast ons en die meneer vroeg iets maar ik verstond het niet. Ik vroeg dus “wat zegt u?” en nog steeds verstond ik zijn antwoord niet. Wij kwamen tenslotte uit Amsterdam en waren niet gewend aan het accent van de chique lui uit het Gooi. Op een gegeven moment zei ik dus “ik hoor u wel, maar ik versta u niet”. 

Dat is een gevleugeld begrip geworden bij ons op de vereniging: ik hoor u wel, maar ik versta u niet.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.title: "Ik hoor u wel, maar ik versta u niet"

http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.description:
Esiste un dipinto di Bruegel il vecchio, denominato “I giochi dei bambini”, in cui viene raffigurato in alto al centro il cosiddetto "Mazza e ppivuzo" (scritto in dialetto rigorosamente torrese). Si tratta della prima rappresentazione di un gioco importato dalle Indie occidentali e che può essere considerato il progenitore del baseball.

Noi, bambini degli anni '50, sapevamo ben poco di questo sport americano, se non grazie a qualche immagine dei cinegiornali dell'epoca, ma le somiglianze ci sono: ad esempio, il battitore doveva colpire al volo il pezzo piccolo di legno. Si giocava, infatti, nel seguente modo: si metteva il pezzo di legno piccolo a terra, in bilico su un poggio, poi con un bastone lo si doveva colpire. Vinceva chi riusciva a lanciarlo il più lontano possibile.

Ciò che sicuramente era diverso rispetto al baseball era la conclusione del gioco. Non avevamo limiti di tempo o di eliminazione, per cui la fine giungeva solo nei casi in cui si rompeva il vetro d’una finestra o si colpiva una persona. Per sfuggire all’ira del malcapitato, era necessario scappare e così il gioco si concludeva con un fuggi-fuggi generale.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.title: "Mazza e ppivuzo", il (quasi) dimenticato emulo del baseball

1-2. Linnea förklarar sitt svar på problemet för läraren, medan Jim tycker att svaret ska vara så här.
3. Daniel och Petra gör tyska-läxan, Stina tittar på. 
4-5. Joel har glömt att göra läxan och skyndar sig att göra den medan andra pratar om 9:ans planerade skolresa.
6. Frida på väg ut ur klassrummet efter teknik-lektionen.

8. Stina är trött på att prata mycket och somnar.

17. Nu har vi satt oss i våra grupper och arbetet kan börja.
18. Vissa har gått ned till biblioteket och letar böcker där.
19. Vi väntar på nyckeln till biblioteket.
20. Mona-Lisa hjälper Andreas att kopiera några papper.
21. Nicklas hittar roliga saker om Kina i en uppslagsbok.
22. Vad ska vi ha med i redovisningen, undrar Camilla, B-M och Theres.
23. Pim, Linnéa och B-M är på väg till idrottslektionen.
24. Killarna spelar basket.
25. Theres och B-M tränar inför basketturneringen.
26-27. Killarna tränar till nästa veckas basketturnering.
28-29. Eva serverar Anna mat i matbespisningen.
30-31. Stina, Linnéa, Petra och Anna-Karin är hungriga.
32. 8:orna kommer till matsalen precis i tid.
33-34. 8:orna står i matkön.
35. - Nu startar jag diskmaskinen, säger Birgitta.
36. Daniel har ingen matlust och vägrar äta.

http://data.europeana.eu/item/847/RIM_it.description:
A medal given to tennis player Björn Borg. Borg was probably awarded the medal when he played basketball at a young age. The medal has been preserved by Björn Borg’s mother Margareta.

Text on Medal
VICTORY GRP. C
BOYS 1969-70

Björn Borg (1956-) is a Swedish former professional tennis player, regarded as one of the world’s foremost in sport of all time. Borg won eleven singles titles in Grand Slam tournaments in 1974-1981, five of them straight in the Wimbledon Championships, six in the French Open and four US Open. During his active career, Borg won a total of 63 singles and 4 doubles titles. Borg was admitted in 1987 to the International Tennis Hall of Fame and in 2003 to the Swedish Tennis Hall of Fame.

http://data.europeana.eu/item/847/RIM_it.description:
Basketball wheelchair from the 1980s used by Lars “Lövis” Löfström (1955-2016).

Löfström was best known as an athlete in a wheelchair, sprinter. He began his sporting career at the Norrbacka Institute. He has participated in four different Swedish national teams between 1971-2004, including wheelchair basketball 1971-1984 and 1994-1997.

After a road accident in his age five, Lars “Lövis” Löfström (1955-2016) suffered a spinal cord injury that made him unable to walk. Through sport, “Promise” gained outlets for its creativity, movement and lust. As a seventeen-year-old, 1972, “Lövis” won his first Paralympic gold medal in a wheelchair slalom in Heidelberg, West Germany.

In total, he participated in eight Paralympic games in which he competed in basketball, athletics, bench press and sailing. In total, Lövis has taken five gold, six silver and three bronze.

In parallel with the sports career, Lars trained for sports teachers at GIH. In 1999 he was involved in the Joriel school. A compulsory school and special school for pupils with neurological disabilities. There he appeared as assistant principal and taught football, orientation and dance.

The wheelchair can be seen in Riksidrottsmuseum’s exhibition The time.

http://data.europeana.eu/item/318/marc_n.description: Former Laker megastar "Magic" Johnson played in a charity game in Jerusalem on Thursday - to raise both awareness about AIDS and funds to help fight the disease. His team - a team of ‘AII-Stars' were pitted against a team of Knesset Members (MKs). The All-Stars won 18:6. Johnson had before the game told reporters he was “thrilled" to be in Israel where the "crowds are crazy about the game". He added that Tel Aviv's beauty had far exceeded his expectations - reminding him in fact of Los Angeles. When Johnson was asked whether he was in Israel to identify with the peace process he replied only that he was “a man of peace”. On Michael Jordan's retirement, “Magic" said he had been sorry to hear about it but that had understood it. http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.description:
Colecție personală de fotografii - Demostene Șofron.

Colecția cuprinde imagini cu baschetbaliști clujeni, jucători și antrenori la cluburile locale, campioni naționali și intenaționali.

Demostene Șofron este jurnalist și comentator sportiv din 1990. Este absolvent al Facultății de Litere (1986) și al Facultății de Educație Fizică și Sport (2000). A fost arbitru divizionar de volei (1977-2013), arbitru de tenis de masă (2014 - în prezent), arbitru de automobilism carting moto (1987- în prezent). Redactor sportiv la cotidianul „Făclia de Cluj” din 1984 până în prezent.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.title: Baschetul clujean în fotografii

http://data.europeana.eu/item/847/RIM_it.description:
Programaffisch för bobsleigh 1954.

Bobsleigh, även bob, är en sport där två-fyra personer åker med en slags täckt släde nerför en lång isbana. Sporten utvecklades av engelsmän i Schweiz från 1870-talet och är från och med 1924 en olympisk gren.

Text på affisch;
"BOBSLEIGH
I TANTOLUNDEN SÖNDAGEN 7 mars 1954 KL.13.00
*
Program
Stockholmsmästerskap i RODEL med deltagare ur Sveriges
OLYMPIATRUPP
En sensation för Sverige
*
Pojkbobstävling
i 2-mansbob med deltagare i åldern 13-18 år
Entré: Vuxna 1:- Barn 50 öre Arr.: Stockholms Bobsleighklubbo. Högalids Ungdomsråd
Garanti-Tryck, Sthlm 1954"

http://data.europeana.eu/item/916105/bhm.description:
Det första DM i brottning ägde rum i april 1922. Uddevalla Atletklubb tog då alla titlarna. Mästarna blev från bantam- till tungvikt: Arvid Järnkvist, Viktor Uddgren, Erik Haak, Sten Forsberg, Erik Börjesson och Einar Jönsson. UAK tränade på hotell royal, som låg vid Lagerbergsgatan 3, ägaren Blomstrand var själv brotningsintresserad. Kortet är taget en söndagsmorgon 1922 av Thure Nihlén och visar Uddevalla Atletklubbs brottare och boxare.
Från vänster: Frömre raden: Nils Andersson, Ivar Kullberg, John Johansson. Andra raden: Rupert Pettersson, Albert Ström, John Samuelsson, Einar Jönsson, Viktor Uddgren, Henry Olsson, Arvid Järnkvist, Taylor Johansson. Tredje raden: Sten Forsberg, Helge Lohmander, Gösta Eriksson, Erik Haak, Gustaf Nilsson, Calle Lohmander, John Andreasson, Knut Olsson, Gustaf Öhlander. Översta raden: Ernst Larsson, Okänd, Knut Algurin, Ludvig Olsson, Gottfrid Pettersson, Okänd, Johan Hermansson, Erik Börjesson.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/916105/bhm.title: Enligt tidigare noteringar: "Ateljefoto av boxare och brottare i Uddevalla."
http://data.europeana.eu/item/916105/bhm.creator: Nihlén, Thure

http://data.europeana.eu/item/91639/SMVK.description: Beaten brass, Cylindrical body and flat base, lock and engraved and inlaid with silver and copper. Surface on body divided into three horizontal registers. Upper and lower feature a plain plate motif outlining the central register where triangles filles with arabesque form an ondulating register. attached to these triangles, arabesque blossoms alternately hang down or up. In these arabesques there are still traces of copper and silver inlay.

http://data.europeana.eu/item/990/item_H.description: Das Bild gliedert sich von der Handlung her deutlich in zwei Hälften. In der linken Hälfte sitzen zwei Jünglinge an einem Tisch, sie werden beim Schachspiel (vermutlich) unterbrochen. Von rechts drängen mehrere Personen in den Kerker ein, darunter drei Soldaten. Ein unbewaffneter Mann in der Mitte der Gruppe verliest ein Dokument. - Durch das vergitterte Fenster ist der Vesuv sichtbar. - Bei den beiden Jünglingen handelt es sich um den letzten Staufer Konradin und seinen Gefährten und Vetter Friedrich von Baden, die im Oktober 1268 im Kerker in Neapel einsitzen und auf ihr Todesurteil warten.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/990/item_H.title: Die Verurteilung Konradins von Schwaben

http://data.europeana.eu/item/951/Cultur.description: Pe verticală este construită, într-un desen cu multă hașură, o compoziție cu două personaje. Un bărbat, redat cu spatele, așezat este față în față cu o femeie, redată tot așezat, din profil dreapta, în stânga sus. Cei doi au între ei o masă pe care se observă o tablă de șah. Fundalul puternic hașurat indică un interior. Trăsăturile personajelor sunt limitate la contururile ascuțite ale corpurilor. Linia desenului este alertă, nervoasă și foarte vibrată. Lucrarea este semnată ilizibil cu creionul, în dreapta jos și datată: „45”.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/951/Cultur.title: Șah
http://data.europeana.eu/item/951/Cultur.creator: Beiu Angheluță, Corina

În partea înferioară, într-un cartuș decorativ, anul 1943. Revers: o tablă de șah cu pioni dedesubt. În jur, pe trei laturi, un chenar decorativ. În partea inferioară, legenda "FEDERATIA/ ROMANA DE SAH".

http://data.europeana.eu/item/951/Cultur.description: Interior cu un grup de persoane așezate în jurul unei mese rotunde. În prim-plan, cu spatele la privitor, o doamnă îmbrăcată elegant citește. În planul al doilea, doi domni îmbrăcați în haine de culoare închisă, sunt concentrați asupra unui joc de șah. Tușă împăstată, pensulație evidentă, manieră post-impresionistă. Semnat și datat: D. Hîrlescu (1)912.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/951/Cultur.title: Jucătorii de șah
http://data.europeana.eu/item/951/Cultur.creator: Hîrlescu Dimitrie

http://data.europeana.eu/item/951/Cultur.description: Într-un desen liniar, realist și minuțios sunt redate pe verticală, mai multe personaje. Cinci bărbați îmbrăcați simplu, cu cămăși, pantaloni și purtând căciuli sau pălării pe cap, sunt agrenați într-o partidă de șah. Așezați pe o bancă sau stând în jurul ei, nici unuia dintre personaje nu i se poate distinge chipul. În marginea din dreapta, jos se zărește o parte de cale ferată iar în registrul superior, redat cu negru compact se află trenul în mișcare. Personajul din spatele băncii privește întors spre tren, în timp ce toți ceilalți sunt concentrați pe joc. Compoziția este dinamică și deschisă. Lucrarea este semnată autograf și datată în partea dreaptă, jos, cu creion: „a.cudinoff 1962”.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/951/Cultur.title: În gară
http://data.europeana.eu/item/951/Cultur.creator: Cudinoff, Anatolie

http://data.europeana.eu/item/951/Cultur.description: Pe verticală ies în evidență, de pe fundalul compact negru, patru personaje. Acestea au hainele și trăsăturile conturate cu ocru, galben și câteva dungi de alb. Cei patru tineri sunt dispuși în jurul unei mese fiind angrenați într-o partidă de șah. Doi jucători sunt dispuși față în față, pe diagonala imaginii. Fiecare are câte un braț ridicat gânditor la cap. Ceilalți doi bărbați privesc spre jocul celor doi, unul fiind așezat la masă cu ei iar celălalt stând în picioare, în spatele jucătorului suprins frontal. În dreapta, spre fundal se evidențiază o tablă de șah liberă. Atmosfera este întunecată și încordată, sublinată și de modalitatea de redare a personajelor, fără accent pe conturarea lor completă sau pe redarea trăsăturilor chipurilor. Lucrarea este semnată ilizibil și datată (1)959, în partea dreaptă, jos, cu creion albastru.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/951/Cultur.title: Tineri colectiviști
http://data.europeana.eu/item/951/Cultur.creator: Dăscălescu, Mihai

http://data.europeana.eu/item/951/Cultur.description: Pe o masă de formă dreptunghiulară, cu tăblia în formă de șah (pătrate gri și negre) se află un ghiveci de flori în tonuri de: alb, galben, gri. Un scaun brun închis în colțul din dreapta mesei. Fond brun roșcat mai închis pe latura dreaptă.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/951/Cultur.title: Natură statică
http://data.europeana.eu/item/951/Cultur.creator: Bartok Francisc

http://data.europeana.eu/item/9200579/kp.description: Photograph of 4 adult female parasitoid wasps on the base of the egg-laying organ (ovipositor) of a large bush cricket female. When the cricket lays her eggs the wasps will descend the ovipositor, quickly laying their own eggs inside those of the cricket. This 'riding' behaviour is called 'phoresy' and is probably far more widespread in parasitoids than presently known. This parasitoid is a new species, each approximately 1 mm in length.

http://data.europeana.eu/item/648/item_G.description:
Schwarzweißfotografie, Außenaufnahme Reichssportfeld, 1950 

Im Zentrum des Bildes befindet sich ein viereckiges, aus Brettern gebautes, zweistöckiges Häuschen, dunkel gestrichen. Der vordere Rand des flachen Daches ist versehen mit einer weißen Zierleiste. Mit weißen Großbuchstaben steht darunter: Cricket-Pavillon. Unter dem Schriftzug befindet sich eine Art Loggia, in der sich vier Männer aufhalten, welche eine Szene weiter weg zu beobachten scheinen. Sie tragen zum Teil kurzärmlige Shirts. Rechts, neben der Loggia gibt es ein Tafelfeld mit den Angaben: Total Runs 42, Wickets 2, Last Man 0, 15. Es scheint gerade ein Spiel ausgetragen zu werden.
Im unteren Teil des Pavillons, also Parterre, gibt es eine Reihe Fenster mit weißen schmalen Rahmen. 

Der Pavillon steht auf einem breiten Streifen Sand, ringsherum befindet sich Rasen, hier wachsen verstreut einige Blumen. Dicht vor dem Pavillon steht eine längere, dunkel gestrichene Bank. Rechts und links des Gebäudes befindet sich jeweils eine Absperrung, in die Erde gesteckte weiße, schmale Stäbe, die mit weiß gestrichenen Ketten verbunden sind. Innerhalb der Absperrung stehen, direkt vor dem Gebäude , 4 weiße Gartenstühle in Reihe. Links vom Pavillon befindet sich ein hoher weißer Fahnenmast. Links dahinter ist eine Peitschenleuchte zu sehen, an der eine lange Leiter lehnt. Weiter dahinter gibt es ein kleines fensterloses Gebäude und einige Sträucher und Bäume.

Rechts im Hintergrund stehen ebenfalls Sträucher und ein Baum, weiter weg sind zwei hohe schmale Türme zu erkennen. 

Bes. Merkmal: im Auftragsbuch ist Herr Jakmuss vermerkt.

Ch. K.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/648/item_G.title: Fotografie Cricket-Pavillon

http://data.europeana.eu/item/847/RIM_it.description:
One of two shields with a complete collection of vassal top marks from 1923-2022. The needle marks are mounted on shields. The marks are published annually in 1923. In 1922, a paper mark was issued, which is missing in this collection. In some years, two variants were issued, and in other years the race was set and no mark was issued.

The badges are collected by Adéle and Per-Axel Wiktorsson. In the period 1973-2001 they were spectators at the finish of the Vasaloppet in Mora. They found the brand 1973 unusually beautiful and subsequently began collecting vassal top marks. Brands before 1973 they have acquired through purchase. They never participated as skiers in Vasaloppet, but were very enthusiastic spectators.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/847/RIM_it.title: Shield

Kuvassa OTK:n hiihtokilpailuun osallistujat.

Osuushiihtojen kilpailujen johtaja Simo Tikka ja palkintokokoelma 12.3.1950.
Kuvan takana teksti: "Työväen Akatemian tyttöjä hiihtokilpailussa Vanajanlinnassa Sirola-opistolaisia vastaan vuonna 1954."
Kuvassa osanottajia Osuuskeskusten Urheilijain hiihtokilpailuihin 17.2.1946.
Henkilökunnan Kerhon hiihtokilpailut pidettiin Kerhoniemessä 5.3.1972. Kilpailijoita oli 37, joista naisia oli 24 ja miehiä 13.
Kuvassa OTK:n naistenhiihdon osanottajat 25.3.1942.

Kuvan takana teksti: "Tainionkosken Tähti ja/tai Enson Koitto: vasemmalta lukien Voitto ja Hanna Kuittinen, Pauli Jouhki, Leila Kuittinen (myöhemmin Jouhki), Matti Kallio sekä Taisto Kuittinen. Edessä Väinö Laakso".
Kuvassa meneillään hiihtokilpailut, katsojat kerääntyneet lähtöpaikalle. Kuva otettu Enson työväentalon edessä. Kuvan takana olevien tietojen mukaan kuvassa näkyvällä paikalla oli vuonna 1980 tehdas.
Kuva OTK:n henkilökunnan hiihtokilpailusta.
Vaasalaisia työläisnuoria hiihtämässä.

Kuva henkilökunnan hiihtokilpailusta 1937.

Hiihtoretkellä helmikuun 25päivä 1934.

http://data.europeana.eu/item/2064105/Mu.description: BILJARD med tillbehör Bestående av spelbord, tolv köer, åtta bollar, pyramid med tjugotvå bollar jämte triangel, fiol, bollskjutare, poängtavla med räkneställning och fack för bollar och krita, två köställ, kritor samt spelregler. Spelbord (tysk biljard) Av valnötsträ. Rektangulärt, på åtta låga ben, med kryss och fotram. Massivt, delvis snidat samt polerat. Inom ramen en nedsänkt skiva, s k taffel av vit marmor, kring ramens inkanter en snett överskjutande karm av gummi, s k vall. Skiva och vall klädda med grönt kläde. Höjd: 86,5 cm; längd: 277 cm; bredd: 153 cm Köer Av flera träslag. Svarvade, avspetsade uppåt samt polerade. Alla köerna upptill med två korta ändstycken, det inre av ebenholts, det yttre av elfenben, ytterst en tjock läderskiva. På nedre änden en dylik läderskiva, rakt avskuren ett kort stycke från plattningen. Längd: 139 - 143 cm Bollar, trettio stycken, av elfenben. En röd och en blå (karambolbollar), en gul (karolina) samt fem vita. Diameter: 6 cm Tjugotvå stycken (pyramid) med låda: Tjugoen vita och en röd (spelbollen) Låda av valnötsträ, bonad. Bollar, diameter: 5,5 cm Låda, höjd: 5,3 cm; sidlängd: 42,5 cm Fiol Av björk och furu samt polerad. Avlång tjock skiva av björk, i kanterna vinkel- formade inskärningar, tre i vardera långsidan och en i vardera änden. Längd: 147,5 cm Bollskjutare Av lönn och furu samt polerad. Fyrsidig klots (huvud) , något böjd och avsmalnande inåt samt med platt ytterända, i inre änden ett skaft som fiolens. Längd: 146 cm Poängtavla (insatt i väggpanelens vänstra skåp i Biljardrummet) Av skiffer. Stående rektangulär, längs vänstra sidan numren 1-10, graverade och förgyllda. Tavla och ställning i ram av valnötsträ med profilerade kanter. Höjd: 126,5 cm; bredd: 47,8 cm Köställ (insatta i väggpanelens båda skåp i Biljardrummet) Av valnötsträ. Bestående av två lister, den ena med en ingripen stav längs fram- kanten, liggande på botten samt med runda försänkningar, klädda med grönt kläde och avpassade för köernas nedre ändar. Kritor (alabaster-), sex stycken Kubformade, fem sidor klädda med papper i rutmönster. Sidlängd: 2,5 cm Två kritor något använda. Spelregler Rektangulärt blad, uppfodrat på blå grå kartong samt med fyrspaltig text. Tryckt på Central-Tryckeriet, Stockholm. Kartong, höjd: 50 cm; bredd: 45 cm Biljard med 12 köer, 7 bollar och 2 räknebrickor utförd efter beställning av Walther och Wilhelmina von Hallwyl hos snickaren och biljardfabrikören F U Aspengren, Stockholm 1897. Ritningarna utförda på professor I G Clasons ritkontor.

http://data.europeana.eu/item/847/RIM_it.description:
Ett par filtade curlingskor från 1960-talet. Likadana såldes i Köpings Sportaffär.

Karl Johan "Köping" Gustafsson (1888-1960) var en svensk fotbollsspelare, känd som den första målgöraren i Sveriges allra första fotbollslandskamp, mot Norge 1908. Gustafsson vann två SM-guld med Djurgårdens IF och deltog i tre olympiska spel (1908, 1912 och 1920). Efter sin aktiva karriär öppnade han en sportaffär i hemstaden Köping.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/847/RIM_it.title: Sko

http://data.europeana.eu/item/847/RIM_it.description:
En curlingborste använd av svenska curlingspelaren/skippen Anette Norberg. Märke Performance.

Anette Norberg (1966-) har vunnit internationella mästerskap som skip för två olika lag med namnet Lag Norberg. Hon har tagit två olympiska guld, 2006 och 2010, samt tre världsmästerskaps-guld och sju europamästerskaps-guld. Totalt tog hon 23 mästerskapsmedaljer mellan 1984 och 2011. 2013 avslutade Norberg sin curlingkarriär.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/847/RIM_it.title: Borste

and
During His May The High Patronage
Stockholm’s Swimming Company.
with the purpose of seeking to promote swimming art in an appropriate way and bringing
unity and cohesion in efforts to this end,
has the honour of its 100th anniversary
JUBILEE DIPLOMA
to
Miss Selma Abdersson’.

Selma Andersson (1894-1993) was a Swedish swimming jumper. She competed in the 1912 Olympic Games in Stockholm (7th Raka Hope) and 1920 in Antwerp (unplaced Raka Hope). Andersson competed for Stockholm’s KK

http://data.europeana.eu/item/323/S_BL_p.description:
Competition in the Tinner basin with i.a. Finnish participants.
The Tinner Basin was opened on 19 June 1938. The final design of the plant was created by the city architect Sten Westholm. The time-typical entrance, dressing and restaurant building is largely untouched since its construction. The driving political force behind the bath was the merchant Axel Brunsjö. In some circles, the Bath was called Brunsjö, after the merchant’s great commitment to the Bath and later became the foreman of the Bath.

http://data.europeana.eu/item/2058611/_k.description: Fasnachtshelge, bemaltes weisses Papier mit Mundartversen ergänzt. Sujet: Aargauer Pferderenntage; grosses Pferd mit Reiter, fünf ZuschauerinnenEin Sujet mit Familienbezug: Der Vater des Helgenmalers war Mitglied des Aargauischen Rennvereins und besuchte regelmässig die Pferderennen im Aarauer Schachen. Dabei dürfte in jungen Jahren des Öfteren auch sein Sohn dabei gewesen sein, der die dortige Atmosphäre offensichtlich als sexuell aufgeladen erlebt hat. Dies inspirierte ihn zu einem «ausserkantonalen» Helgen mit einem Geschehen, das rund 20 Kilometer von «Linde» entfernt stattfand. Im Aarauer Schachen, dem Exerziergelände der Infanterie- und Kavallerieschulen, war 1921 erstmals ein Jagdrennen über 3800 Meter für Offiziere mit Dienstpferden der Schweizer Armee durchgeführt worden. Solche Rennen gibt es noch heute.Max Rickenbacher-Hufschmid malte diesen und weitere Fasnachtshelgen ungefähr zwischen 1952 und 1962 als Fasnachtsdekoration für das Restaurant "Linde" in Sissach, das seine Eltern betrieben.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/2058611/_k.title: Fasnachtshelge "Aarauer Renntage"
http://data.europeana.eu/item/2058611/_k.creator: Rickenbacher-Hufschmid, Max

http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.description:
This is the Wagener Stadium and sports complex in Amstelveen, Netherlands on the outskirts of Amsterdam.

It is mostly used for hockey matches, and has been owned by the Dutch Hockey Association since 1980.

It was built by the Amsterdam Hockey & Bandy Club in 1939. Its name honours the club's president, Joop Wagener.

The stadium has been renovated several times, and hosted major national and international hockey tournaments.

http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.description:
Hockey Team, Dominican Convent, Taylor’s Hill, Galway, Ireland, c 1912, featuring 11 young ladies, all with [white] high collared blouses, striped ties and dark shirts.  The front row is holding hockey sticks. The group are standing outside beside a rough building and bare leaved tree trunks, with some railings visible in the background. 

Several names are handwritten in ink on the photograph indicating, K E Tennant; P Tennant; M. Casey, BA; M Tennant in the back row; and in the front M J Donovan, MA; E Paul; K O’Doherty BA.

The image is part of a larger archive collection, the Mack / Warren-Thompson Collection (IE GCCA / GP11/), dating from 1825-1991.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.title: Ladies' Hockey Team, 1912

http://data.europeana.eu/item/2022703/pa.description: Lourdes Artime, jugadora de la Agrupación Deportiva Femenina hockey, Gijón/Xixón (Asturias).  El fotógrafo Constantino Suárez (Gijón/Xixón, 1899-1983), fue reportero gráfico de varios periódicos y revistas durante los años veinte y treinta. Sus imágenes poseen un extraordinario valor para documentar la vida cotidiana de Gijón/Xixón (Asturias), especialmente entre 1920 y 1937. Por las circunstancias que le tocó vivir, se convirtió en un adelantado de lo que hoy se llama fotoperiodismo, siempre atento a los hechos ordinarios y extraordinarios de su tiempo. Destaca por la fuerza de las imágenes que tomó en primera línea durante la Revolución de Octubre de 1934 y en el frente y la retaguardia durante la Guerra Civil, desde el bando republicano. A pesar de que desde 1937 su trayectoria profesional estuvo marcada por la cárcel y la represión, continuó siempre haciendo fotos. Tuvo el cuidado de conservar miles de imágenes capaces de escribir por sí solas la historia social de Gijón/Xixón y de Asturias durante décadas.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/2022703/pa.title: Negativo fotográfico
http://data.europeana.eu/item/2022703/pa.creator: Suárez Fernández, Constantino (Lugar de nacimiento: Gijón-Xixón (capital), 24/02/1899 - Lugar de defunción: Gijón-Xixón (capital), 25/02/1983)

http://data.europeana.eu/item/951/Cultur.description: Lucrarea face parte din ciclul „Dobrogea”. Ea este semnată (cu pix albastru) în colțul din dreapta jos: „eugenia iftodi”. Artista a pictat un golf la mare. Vederea este panoramică. Intensitatea cromatică a malului (registrul inferior) contrastează cu norii. În depărtare se observă două bărci cu pânze și o peninsulă cu vegetație bogată. Petele sunt transparente și semitransparente. Paleta de culoare conține: galben, ocru, oranj, galben-verde, verde, gri, bleu, turcoaz, maron.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/951/Cultur.title: Golf la mare

http://data.europeana.eu/item/90402/RP_P.description: This is an unusual composition. Prominently in view is a man relaxing at a table, but it is the brightly illuminated ringball player behind the partition, who draws our attention. He drives the ball with his club, while two gentlemen wait their turn. This etching affords only a glimpse of the country inn and of the ringball alley. It therefore seems like a randomly chosen detail, a moment in time captured ‘from life’.

This coin commemorates the 45th World Championship Greek-Roman Wrestling in Athens, 1999.

Greek-Roman wrestling is especially popular in Europe, but it is practised throughout the world. The contestants must apply all holds above the waist, and the use of the legs in scoring or defending is prohibited. Accordingly, tripping, tackling, and using the legs to secure a hold.

http://data.europeana.eu/item/91617/upmu.description:
Nordiskt förbund för kvinnogymnastik har kurs för 225
kvinnliga gymnaster i Sigtuna 1935. Deltagarna kom för att
ta del av Elli Björksténs gymnastiksystem. Hon ansåg att
tidigare gymnastik varit för könsneutral och hade utvecklat
en egen form för kvinnor.
Den kom att ha stor påverkan. Enligt de nya riktlinjerna
kunde flickor och pojkar utföra samma övningar fram
till puberteten. Men då skildes de åt. Åtskillnaden gällde
även under 1940- och 1950-talen, till och med ända in på
1960-talet, enligt en undersökning som Skolöverstyrelsens
gymnastikkonsulenter gjorde 1962.

http://data.europeana.eu/item/916123/SLM.description:
Smideshammare från Råby krog, Edstorp 

"Kommer från Råby krog".
Ett antal föremål (främst smidesverktyg) ingår i en serie som kommer från smeden och torparen Karl Ulrik Ledberg (1844-1926) som bodde vid Råby krog, Edstorp, mellan åren 1890-1916. Sannolikt från 1916 då änklingen Karl Ulrik flyttade med sin dotter till Trosa. Ytterligare föremål inköptes vid en auktion i Trosa efter hans död 1926. 
Eftersom fadern var spiksmed vid Forssjö bruk (spiksmedjan), och liksom flera i familjen Ledberg knutna till Forssjö bruk kan man tänka sig att (åtminstone delar av) de ålderdomliga verktygen och redskapen kommer från fadern.

http://data.europeana.eu/item/916106/vbg.description:
Data spel för Play Station . Spelet är ett ishockeyspel.
 

Inför millennieskiftet översvämmades marknaden av produkter, av mer eller mindre kortlivad natur, som skulle minna om detta högst ovanliga kalenderskifte. År 2000 hade länge stått som symbol för framtiden - inte minst i olika sciencefictionskildringar, och det fanns många spekulationer om olika olyckor som skulle inträffa vid just detta skifte. Men när nyårsraketerna försvunnit upp i den dimtunga nyårsnatten och när nyårsmorgonen grydde fann man att världen var ungefär som dagen innan.


Föremålet ingår i en samling med tema Millennium och år 2000 som Calle Göse samlat in under några år.

Gåvan är riktad till Vänersborgs museum.

http://data.europeana.eu/item/847/RIM_it.description:
En medalj given till tennisspelaren Björn Borg. Borg har fått medaljen när han spelade ishockey 1969. Medaljen har bevarats av Björn Borgs mamma Margareta.

Text på medalj:
SEGR. GRP. C.
1969

Björn Borgs far Rune var en duktig bordtennisspelare, vilket inspirerade Björn att börja spela tennis. Björn spelade även ishockey under sin ungdom. Björn slog igenom tidigt och spelade redan 1972 som 15-åring Davis Cup för Sverige.

Björn Borg (1956-) är en svensk före detta professionell tennisspelare, ansedd som en av världens främsta inom sporten genom tiderna. Borg vann under 1974–1981 elva singeltitlar i Grand Slam-turneringar, varav fem raka i Wimbledonmästerskapen, sex i Franska öppna och fyra US Open. Under sin aktiva karriär vann Borg totalt 63 singel- och 4 dubbeltitlar. Borg upptogs 1987 i International Tennis Hall of Fame och 2003 i Swedish Tennis Hall of Fame.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/847/RIM_it.title: Medalj

http://data.europeana.eu/item/847/RIM_it.description:
A medal given to tennis player Björn Borg. Borg has received the medal when he played ice hockey in 1969. The medal has been preserved by Björn Borg’s mother Margareta.

Text on Medal
CITY OF STOCKHOLMS
SPORTS AND
OUTDOOR BOARD
ICE HOCKEY 1969

Björn Borg’s father Rune was a talented table tennis player, which inspired Björn to start playing tennis. Björn also played ice hockey during his youth. Björn struck through early and played back in 1972 as a 15-year-old Davis Cup for Sweden.

Björn Borg (1956-) is a Swedish former professional tennis player, regarded as one of the world’s foremost in sport of all time. Borg won eleven singles titles in Grand Slam tournaments in 1974-1981, five of them straight in the Wimbledon Championships, six in the French Open and four US Open. During his active career, Borg won a total of 63 singles and 4 doubles titles. Borg was admitted in 1987 to the International Tennis Hall of Fame and in 2003 to the Swedish Tennis Hall of Fame.

http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.description:
Pe 9 decembrie 2016, la Sala Polivalentă din Cluj-Napoca, a avut loc  spectacolul „Kings on Ice”. 

Show-ul de clasa mondială a fost unic prin perfecțiunea, pasiunea și strălucirea cu care patinatorii s-au dedicat momentului artistic, acompaniați de către inconfundabila Vienna Strauss Orchestra și de sunetele magnifice ale viorii Stradivarius.

Spectacolul a adus în premieră pentru România renumiţi patinatori şi acrobaţi. Alături de multiplul campion mondial Evgeni Plushenko, supranumit „Țarul gheții”, au participat și Brian Joubert, Stephane Lambiel şi Adelina Sotnikova, prima campioană olimpică din istoria patinajului artistic feminin din Rusia. 

Surpriza ediției a fost faimoasa pereche de acrobaţi pe gheaţă, Alexander Liubchenko (din Ucraina) şi Jean-Denis Sanchis (din Franţa). Aceştia au intrat în Cartea Recordurilor pentru cea mai lungă săritură pe spate - de 6,09 metri. Ei au prezentat exerciţii spectaculoase, dificile, care nu sunt permise în competiţiile sportive.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.title: Kings on Ice

Eric Waite, who is taking a leading part in the ice ballet 'Marina' which the Queen is to see at the Empress Stadium, Earls Court, on Wednesday, was at Paddington station to greet his fiancee, Miss Dorothy Bolton, on arrival from Memphis, Tennessee, aboard the 'Queen Mary' boat train._x000D_
Mr Olsen came over from America, especially to see her fiance on the ice._x000D_
It is expected that the couple will get married in England._x000D_
22 November 1937

http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.description:
Clubul Sportiv “Universitatea” Cluj, cu cele 21 secţii,  reprezintă tradiţia sportivă, continuitatea şi performanţa în sport, de la 1919 şi până în prezent, fiind una din entităţile ce se identifică cu istoria Clujului şi a Transilvaniei ultimilor 100 de ani.

În prezent, sub sigla „U” îşi desfăşoară activitatea 21 de secţii sportive, atât pe echipe cât şi în discipline individuale: atletism, baschet masculin şi feminin, handbal masculin şi feminin, judo, rugby masculin şi feminin, volei masculin şi feminin, culturism&fitness, scrabble, tir sportiv, tenis, patinaj viteză, box, lupte, echitaţie, scrimă, schi fond și natație.

--- English translation ---

Activities of the Universitatea Cluj-Napoca Sports Club 1919

Universitatea Cluj Sports Club, with its 21 sections, represents sports tradition, continuity and sport performance from 1919 to the present, being one of the entities that identifies itself with the history of Cluj and Transylvania for the last 100 years. 

Currently, under the “U” logo, there are 21 sports sections - both in teams and individually, men and women: athletics, basketball, handball, judo, rugby, volleyball, bodybuilding & fitness, scrabble, shooting, tennis, speed skating, boxing, wrestling, horse racing, fencing, cross-country skiing and swimming.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.title: Din activitatea Clubului sportiv „Universitatea” Cluj-Napoca 1919

http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.description:
J’adore le judo, j’ai vu beaucoup de films et de vidéos sur ce sport.

Mes copains en font également.

Moi, j’ai ma ceinture blanche.

Le premier jour de cours , je stressais et j’ai même oublié mon kimono.

Le deuxième jour, nous avons fait des prises et j’ai pleuré et au moment où vous lisez ce texte, j’ai encore mal !

J’ai également plein de blessures.

Malgré tout cela, je m’accroche !

--- English translation --- 

You have to hang on

I love judo. I've seen a lot of movies and videos about this sport. 

My friends do it, too. 

I've got my white belt. 

On the first day of class, I was stressed and I even forgot my kimono. 

On the second day, we took the shots and I cried and, even by the time you read this text, I'm still in pain! 

I also have a lot of injuries. 

Despite all this, I keep going!
http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.title: Il faut s'accrocher

http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.description:
Colecție personală de fotografii - Demostene Șofron 

Colecția cuprinde imagini cu karatiști clujeni, jucători și antrenori la cluburile locale, campioni naționali și intenaționali.

Demostene Șofron este jurnalist și comentator sportiv din 1990. Este absolvent al Facultății de Litere (1986) și al Facultății de Educație Fizică și Sport (2000). A fost arbitru divizionar de volei (1977-2013), arbitru de tenis de masă (2014 - în prezent), arbitru de automobilism carting moto (1987- în prezent). Redactor sportiv la cotidianul „Făclia de Cluj” din 1984 până în prezent.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.title: Karatiști clujeni

http://data.europeana.eu/item/2021648/re.description: Witte judojas, van Anton Geesink. Sportman van het jaar 1961, 1964 en 1965. In 1957 Sporter van het jaar. Anton Geesink is een van Nederlands grootste sporthelden. Zo werd de judoka drie maal wereldkampioen en 21 maal Europees kampioen. Bij de Olympische Spelen van 1964 in Tokyo behaalde de zwaargewicht één van de meest indrukwekkende successen uit de Nederlandse sportgeschiedenis. Hij versloeg de Japanner Akio Kaminaga op eigen bodem en was de eerste Nederlandse olympische kampioen judo. In 2005 kreeg hij van NOC*NSF de Fanny Blankers-Koen Carrièreprijs. Merk Rucanor.

http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.description:
Federatia Romana de Karate WKC (FRK WKC) a luat fiinta in mai 2000 prin decizia Ministerului Tineretului si Sportului de a recunoaste organizatia noastra in randul federatiilor nationale din Romania.

Radacinile organizatiei noastre dateaza inca din 1997 cand un grup de entuziasti au hotarat sa fondeze Uniunea Wado Ryu Romania (UWRR) in scopul dezvoltarii unei activitati performante in sfera Karate-ului la nivel national si international. Transformarea UWRR in FRK WKC, prin recunoasterea de catre Ministerul Tineretului si Sportului a organizatiei noastre, a fost doar rezultatul normal ce a urmat unei activitati excelente la nivel international, prin obtinerea primului titlu mondial la Bochum 1999.

Misiunea federatiei noastre este promovarea inaltelor valori ale Karate-ului in randul copiilor, tinerilor sau tuturor celor care cred in Artele Martiale, in scopul educarii controlului de sine, a cresterii capacitatilor psihice si fizice a celor care urmeaza calea noastra.

La Campionatele europene de karate pentru copii, cadeți și juniori, organizate la Liege - Belgia, în perioada 3-7 iunie 2015, echipa României s-a clasat pe locul 1, cu 47 de medalii de aur, 31 de argint și 21 de medalii de bronz.

La Campionatele europene de karate pentru copii, cadeți și juniori, organizate la Montichiari, Italia, în perioada 13-16 octombrie 2016, echipa României s-a clasat pe locul 2, cu 59 de medalii de aur, 42 de argint și 21 de medalii de bronz.

La Campionatele europene de la Cluj-Napoca, România 5-9 aprilie 2017, echipa României s-a clasat pe locul 1, cu 75 de medalii de aur, 61 de argint și 62 de medalii de bronz.

La Campionatele europene de la Ta Quali, Malta, 23-28 octombrie 2018, echipa României s-a clasat pe locul 1,  cu 61 de medalii de aur, 38 de argint și 37 de medalii de bronz.

La Campionatele europene de la Odense, Danemarca 27-29 octombrie 2019, echipa României s-a clasat pe locul 1,  cu 85 de medalii de aur, 61 de argint și 36 de medalii de bronz.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.title: Campionate europene la care au participat reprezentanții Federației Române de Karate WUKF

Transformarea UWRR in FRK WKC, prin recunoasterea de catre Ministerul Tineretului si Sportului a organizatiei noastre, a fost doar rezultatul normal ce a urmat unei activitati excelente la nivel international, prin obtinerea primului titlu mondial la Bochum 1999.

Misiunea federatiei noastre este promovarea inaltelor valori ale Karate-ului in randul copiilor, tinerilor sau tuturor celor care cred in Artele Martiale, in scopul educarii controlului de sine, a cresterii capacitatilor psihice si fizice a celor care urmeaza calea noastra.

La Campionatele mondiale de la Dublin, Irlanda, 15-19 iunie 2016, echipa României s-a clasat pe locul 1, cu 49 de medalii de aur, 25 de argint și 19 de medalii de bronz.

La Campionatele mondiale de la Montecatini Terme, Italia, 30 noiembrie - 3 decembrie 2017,  echipa României s-a clasat pe locul 1, cu 51 de medalii de aur, 33 de argint și 27 de medalii de bronz.

La Campionatele mondiale de la Dundee, Scoția, 14-17 iunie 2018,  echipa României s-a clasat pe locul 1, cu 43 de medalii de aur, 31 de argint și 27 de medalii de bronz.

http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.description:
C’était le jour de mon passage de grade au karaté. Il y avait des juges et nous passions par groupe de quatre.

Pour gagner la ceinture, il fallait faire le kata de son choix puis un kata imposé.

J’ai fait un kata Pinan Nidan.

Ce jour-là , j’ai gagné la ceinture de karaté.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.title: La victoire

http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.description:
J’avais 9 ans lorsque qu’un jour, au karaté,  j’ai voulu participer à un concours de kata qui se déroulait sur un stade , je crois que c’était un vendredi.

J’ai fini treizième sur vingt. J’étais un peu déçue  mais je me suis dit : « Ce n’est pas très grave, je ferai mieux la prochaine fois , et puis treizième, c’est la moitié, c’est déjà bien .»

J’aurais vraiment aimé être première, je me suis donnée à fond pour gagner. 

J’ai appris le kata que je connaissais le mieux, je l’avais  répété de nombreuses fois pour être la meilleure.

J’étais un peu triste mais depuis, je m'entraîne à fond pour gagner la prochaine fois.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.title: Mon concours de Karaté

Till kajaken:
Framför hålet en kajakstol som nr. 1207 med hoprullad harpunlina, på spetsen en harpunspets (som nr. 1087), harpunblåsa (nr. 1088) med munstycke och "amulett-stängsel" med snastofs,  bärrem (se 1054), lans med stenspets (se 1127- 28), fågelspjut med fyra spetsar (se 1147), kastträ (nr i orig. kat.4952 eller 4953, se 1142 - 43), båtshake (se 1208), harpunlans med fastsatt förskaft av ben och spetsblad av järn, bunt av brunt skinn med jaktredskap av ben (sårpluggar etc, sannolikt inte från Port Clarence), brunt skinnstycke (lika), tvåbladig paddel (inte Port Clarence) samt en överplagg av sältarm (se 1004) till eskimåmomodellen. (nr. i orig, kat. ett av 5128 - 30). Längd: 470 cm. Bredd: 70 cm. Höjd: ca 35 cm.

http://data.europeana.eu/item/2022703/pa.description: Embarcación de forma alargada de cubierta cerrada. Está realizada con un armazón de madera y caña, revestida de membrana. Hacia la zona media de la cubierta, existe un resalte circular hueco cerrado con una membrana atada con fibra vegetal. El remate de la proa con un apéndice bifurcado es característico de la cultura Chugach. Este tipo de embarcación también era utilizado por los Tlingit de la zona septentrional de la Costa Noroeste de América del Norte. En 1779, José Camacho en su diario describió y esbozó en un dibujo un kayak similar a éste empleado por los Tlingit. Un número importante de sociedades tanto del Ártico como Costa Noroeste pasan una parte destacada de su vida en el mar al ser su mayor fuente de recursos, sin olvidar el aprovechamiento de lagos y ríos. Este hecho ha tenido como resultado que hayan adaptado un buen número de técnicas de caza y navegación a las específicas condiciones del medio ambiente. Las embarcaciones son un buen ejemplo de ello, una de las más características es el kayak, que presenta variaciones en las distintas culturas, pero siempre están realizados a medida para el único tripulante que va a utilizarlo. En ellos atan firmemente mediante pasadores todo el aparejo para la caza y la pesca. Este tipo de kayaks son modelos o maquetas que pueden tener distintas finalidades como la de mostrar de forma didáctica a los más jóvenes la forma de construcción a escala de este tipo de embarcaciones,  también pueden ser juguetes realizados para los niños u obras construidas para la venta, ya que el comercio de este tipo de objetos se desarrolló muy tempranamente ante la demanda de expedicionarios y viajeros a estas regiones. Esta pieza forma parte del conjunto de obras recogidas en el último tercio del siglo XVIII en el transcurso de las distintas expediciones científicas españolas que llegaron hasta esta región.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/2022703/pa.title: Kayak

http://data.europeana.eu/item/1190/INP_p.description: 1. Podul Decebal a fost construit în 1974, are o lungime de 191 metri și o lățime de 11,7 metri și face legătura, peste râul Mureș, între centrul orașului și patru cartiere, dar asigură și accesul spre Ștradul „Neptun” sau Cetatea Aradului. Pentru că se afla în stare avansată de degradare din cauza traficului intens, care ajunge la 20.000 de vehicule pe zi, a fost consolidat și reabilitat în 2019. 2. Hotelul ”Parc”, actual ”Best Western” se află pe malul Mureșului, în centrul istoric al orașului, în imediata apropiere a zonei comericale, într-un peisaj foarte pitoresc și la 450 m de Primăria Arad. Hotelul, aflat într-o stare deplorabilă de mulți ani, a fost cumpărat de către firma Arsat Industrie, care a reabilitat și Vechiul Cazino din Arad, situat vis-a-vis de Hotel Parc, spre nord. În prezent, hotelul se află în curs de reabilitare. 3. Construită în perioada 1902-1911, Biserica (Catedrala) catolică din Arad, „Sfântul Anton de Padova”, a fost proiectată de arhitectul Emil Tabacovici (Milan Tabakovits). Stilul arhitectural este o combinație între baroc și renascentism, începand cu intrarea în biserică, unde coloanele cu capiteluri corintice susțin un antablament decorat și inscripționat deasupra intrării cu citatul „Și va fi casa mea, casa de rugaciune.” Luca: 19:46. Frontonul de deasupra intrării conține o replică a lucrării lui Michelangelo - „Pieta” și este încadrat de o arcadă decorată pe intrados cu rozete. Arhivolta este și ea decorată cu sculpturi reprezentând îngeri. Deasupra cornișei, în trei nișe separate prin mici coloane adosate, se află reprezentările Mariei, Mariei Magdalena și a lui Isus. Cupola se sprijină pe un tambur circular, prevazută cu ferestre separate de asemenea de câte două coloane în stil corintic, adosate. Monumentalitatea edificiului se poate observa și la interior, unde biserica, bazată pe planul într-o singură nava, este mărginită de coloane din marmură în stil corintic, ce susțin sistemul boltit al navei.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/1190/INP_p.title: Arad - pod peste Mureș și Hotel „Parc”
http://data.europeana.eu/item/1190/INP_p.creator: Dumitru Florin Dumitru (photographer)

http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.description:
To mark the launch of the new Mazda 323 in February 1981, the Japanese car manufacturer shot a promotional spot involving Kendo, or Japanese fencing. Filming took place in Limerick, purportedly to avoid using union labour for the film crew. As Kendo was unknown in Ireland at that time, Jock Hopson and Fujii Okimitsu were flown over from the UK. 

This was likely one of the first times that Kendo was practiced in Ireland.

Mazda originally requested two Japanese players, but as only Mr. Fujii was available in the UK at that time, Jock Hopson accompanied him. For the publicity shots Mr. Hopson’s face and arms were covered by the Kendo armour, however the makeup artist insisted on colouring his feet, which were exposed, in order to make him look “more oriental”.

The two were put up in the Limerick Inn Hotel for the weekend at Mazda’s expense with meals provided and a free bar every evening. The actual performance involved practicing kendo on a rotating stage with dry ice “mist”, heavy beat promo music and strobe lighting. Several times they lost each other in the mist and once Mr. Fujii fell off the stage and Mr. Hopson had to continue on his own against an imaginary opponent.

The pair were presented with Hurleys as a memento of the event.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.title: The first time Kendo was practiced in Ireland

http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.description:
During the mid-1990s, Peter Sherriff, who had previously practised Kendo in France, moved to Cork and started a Kendo club there. Shunji Hasunuma, who had moved to Dublin from Japan for work, rented a squash court and found some students, after being told by the Gardaí that he couldn't practice in Phoenix Park.

Shortly after this, the Irish Kendo Federation was formed at a meeting between the Dublin and the Cork clubs. The federation applied for recognition by the European Kendo Federation and International Kendo Federation.

Irish Kendo first participated in the European Kendo Championships in 1999 in Lourdes, France.

Shunji Hasunuma was the coach, and the two clubs between them were able to field a full men's team of seven.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.title: Ireland participates in the European Kendo Championships for the first time

http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.description:
Door een toeval kwam ik in aanraking met Lenie van der Velde, toen zij 90 jaar oud was. In onze gesprekken kwamen wij al snel op sport. Zij had vroeger gekorfbald en gebasketbald. Dat laatste was interessant, want zij begon te basketballen na de oorlog. Ze gaf al aan dat zij in top teams in Nederland speelde, maar ook als international in het Oranjeteam. 

Dat was de aanleiding voor mij om te gaan zoeken op internet. En op Delpher.nl vond ik al snel krantenverslagen van wedstrijden, niet alleen op haar meisjesnaam, maar ook op de naam van haar partner, in een Nederlandse spelling en een internationale (Remeijer en Remeyer). Ook beeldonderzoek bij het Nationaal archief leverde zo’n 15 foto’s op. Bovendien kwam er het nodige statistische materiaal van een ‘onofficiële’ archivaris van het Nederlandse basketbal. Zelf had ook een plakboek met zo’n 60 foto’s en uitgeknipte artikelen. 

Aan de hand van dit tekst- en beeldmateriaal zijn in 2020 en 2021 gesprekken gevoerd over haar sportactiviteiten in korfbal en basketbal na de WO II. Dit leverde interessant audiomateriaal op. Intussen wordt er gewerkt aan een levensboek, dat m.n. een beeld geeft van de opkomst van basketbal na WO II en in het bijzonder dames basketbal, de invloed van de Amerikanen en Canadezen,  de verhouding van heren basketbal en dames basketbal en het internationaal reizen, o.a. naar landen achter het IJzeren Gordijn.

Het levensboek is in november 2021 gereed. Helaas zal de hoofdpersoon het niet meer zien, aangezien zij onlangs is overleden.

--- English translation ---

By chance, I came into contact with Lenie van der Velde, when she was 90 years old. In our conversations, we soon came to sport. She used to play korfball and basketball. The latter was interesting, because she started playing basketball after the war. She mentioned that she played she played in the top teams in the Netherlands, and also as an international in the 'Orange Team'. 

That was the reason for me to start searching on the internet. On Delpher.nl, I quickly found newspaper reports of her competitions, not only with her maiden name, but also with her married name, in both a Dutch and international spelling (Remeijer and Remeyer). Image research at the National Archives also yielded about 15 photos. 

In addition, there was the necessary statistical material from an ‘unofficial’ archivist of the Dutch basketball. He himself also had a scrapbook with about 60 photos and cut-out articles. 

On the basis of this textual and visual material, discussions were held in 2020 and 2021 about her sporting activities in korfball and basketball after the World War II. This produced interesting audio material. In the meantime, a biography is underway, which reflects the rise of basketball after World War II and, in particular, women’s basketball, the influence of Americans and Canadians, the relationship between men’s basketball and women’s basketball and international travel, including to countries behind the Iron Curtain. 

The biography was finalised in November 2021. Unfortunately, the protagonist won't see it anymore, since she died recently.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.title: Dames basketbal na de oorlog

http://data.europeana.eu/item/847/RIM_it.description:
A red sweater with black sleeves and yellow cuffs, ringing and jersey ends. The sweater was used in kabaddi, a team sport originating in India. Branded Bengaluru Bulls, a team from Bengaluru, India.

Kabaddi is a team sport/martial art originating in Punjab in India. Several variants of the sport occur, and it is performed both indoors and outdoors. The modern form of the sport can be traced back to 1920 when the first matches were played in India. Over the years, sports rules have been standardized. Kabaddi has been part of Asian Games since the 1990s (an Asian variant of the Olympic Games). Sweden is a member of the International Kabaddi Federation.

TAEKWONDO OLYMPIC SELECTION
SWEDEN 1999
ETU

ETU står för European Taekwondo Union, som är en officiell organisation för europeisk Taekwondo. 1999 stod Stockholm, Sverige, värd för en av kvalificeringstävlingarna innan de olympiska spelen 2000 i Sydney, Australien.

Taekwondo (ibland skriven även TaeKwonDo eller Taekwon-Do) är en koreansk självförsvar som utvecklades under 1950-talet till egen kampart. Målet med Taekwondo är att utveckla dig själv som människa, mentalt och fysiskt. Taekwondo betyder "Fotens och handens väg". I Sverige är taekwondon organiserad i Svenska Taekwondoförbundet, som grundades 1996.

http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.description:
My name is Chris Dougliss. I practice a form of Martial Arts called Hun Gar Kung Fu. 

I was born in the village of Wombourne near Wolverhampton, in the West Midlands of England.

At the age of seventeen, a friend and I started learning karate. After a short while, I realised it was not for me and I started training in Gar Kung Fu in Dudley.

I trained there for approximately fifteen years becoming a Black Belt, First Degree. I then trained with weapons i.e. sword, staff, spear, trident, butterfly knives and nunchaku. During that time, I made life-long friends including my wife and my best man!

One of my friends introduced me to a form of Kung Fu called Hun Gar which is a less westernised form of the sport. It is based on animal styles including Tiger, Crane, Snake, Mantis, Leopard, Monkey and Drunken Kung Fu. I have trained in this form for the last thirty-six years.

In 1989, with my wife Rose, I moved to Tipperary where her family reside. 
Over the years I have both learned and taught various forms of martial arts including kickboxing, Taekwondo, Hun Gar, Tai Chi and Jujitsu. 

I have met lots of interesting people through my teaching including one young man who became my son-in-law. I have taught people of all ages from seven to sixty. My own daughters started training at the age of five.

Some young people came to learn self-defence because they were quiet and shy and, as a result, were being bullied in school. Martial arts training developed their self-esteem and that new-found confidence was often enough to stop any further bullying without them even lifting a finger.

Martial Arts has been a vital part of my life. As a young man who was shy, it built my confidence and self-esteem. It has also given me discipline, self-control, determination and will-power - all of which have been invaluable to me in all aspects of my life including my careers as an ambulance EMT and as a driving instructor. None more so than when I acquired a work-related back injury that required multiple surgeries. In fact, the neurosurgeon said that without my core strength and fitness level I would have required a permanent walking aid. 

I have modified my training as a result of my back injury: no more spinning back kicks or flying kicks for me! However, it is still an essential part of my daily routine. It is great for developing concentration and improving memory - be it through going through weapon sets or practicing various ‘forms’. 

I would recommend martial arts to any young person who is looking for a form of exercise that develops discipline and focus. For the older person,  it can be adapted to accommodate their personal ability while promoting fitness and flexibility. Aged sixty-three, I still practice daily.

What began as a teenage hobby has, in fact, become a way of life for me. It had a direct impact on where my life took me, introducing me to my future wife and bringing me ‘a long way to Tipperary.’
http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.title: Bringing Hun Gar Kung Fu to Tipperary

http://data.europeana.eu/item/2022703/pa.description: Copia positiva estereoscópica que muestra una cumbre de alta montaña y dos hombres que están rescatando de la nieve a un excursionista herido. Al lado se ven los bastones de montañismo clavados en la nieve. En el cartón azul del soporte secundario lleva impresa la firma A. Braun, à Dornach (haut Rhin) y en la trasera una etiqueta impresa con la inscripción Nº 1858 Station des Grands-Mulets. / Mont-Blanc. Grands-Mulets es un refugio de alta montaña en el macizo de Mont Blanc.  Adolphe Braun (1812-1877) tuvo un establecimiento fotográfico en la ciudad de Dornach, donde contrató a Alexis Gaudin para la producción de imágenes estereoscópicas con vistas de diversos puntos de Europa. Braun acabó creando una gran empresa con más de cien empleados, que reproducía obras de arte de museos y de ciudades de distintos lugares del mundo. Muy popular fue la serie de Suiza, de la que forma parte esta imagen.  La fotografía estereoscópica nos permite ver una imagen con efecto tridimensional, ya que combina dos vistas muy similares pero no idénticas, reproduciendo la visión binocular. En la década de los cuarenta del siglo XIX se experimentó con esta técnica, presentándose los primeros modelos en la Great Exhibition de Londres en 1851. En las décadas siguientes la fotografía estereoscópica alcanzó una gran popularidad y se creó una gran industria con una producción masiva de fotografías mostrando ciudades, paisajes y monumentos de todos los rincones del mundo, así como escenas de género.  Este par estereoscópico pertenece al conjunto The Stereoscopic Treasury, formado por el visor de dicho modelo (Inv. CE10408), a juego con su caja (Inv. CE10407) y su llave (Inv. CE10409) y otros cincuenta y dos pares estereoscópicos (Invs. CE10410-CE10462).   La trasera cuenta con una inscripción manuscrita por W. Furnival, firma que está presente en la caja del conjunto y en muchos pares, lo que hace suponer que fue el coleccionista de tarjetas estereoscópicas propietario de este conjunto The Stereoscopic Treasury.  (Catalogación: Carmen Linés Viñuales. 2023)

http://data.europeana.eu/item/2021009/_F.description:
sisällön kuvaus: Pirkan hiihdon osanottajia saunomassa ja lumessa vilvoittelemassa vuonna 1954. Tunturilatu ry: n 15 jäsentä osallistui Pirkan Ladun avaushiihtoon Niinisalosta Tampereelle.   
  
Professori Lauri Pihkalan aloitteesta seuraavana vuonna 1955 järjestettiin ensimmäinen kaikille avoin Pirkan hiihto, 90 km mittainen laturetki, jossa oli retkihiihdon lisäksi myös kilpasarja. Pirkan hiihdossa haluttiin tarjota tilaisuus nimenomaan pitkän matkan hiihtovaellukseen.   
  
Tunturilatu ry on Lapin retkeilyyn ja retkeilyyn erikoistunut urheilujärjestö, joka kuuluu Suomen Ladun jäsenjärjestöihin. Suomen Latu perustettiin vuonna 1938 edistämään kansanurheilua.

http://data.europeana.eu/item/2021009/_D.description:
sisällön kuvaus: Participants of Pirkka ski race in 1954. 15 members from Tunturilatu ry participated in the opening event of Pirkka ski track from Niinisalo to Tampere in 1954.    
  
First public Pirkka ski race was organized one year later in 1955, after professor Lauri Pihkala`s proposition. He and other members of Tunturilatu ry wanted to increase the popularity of long distance ski touring.  The route of Pirkka ski race was 90 km long and there were hiking and racing series.  
  
Tunturilatu ry is a sport organization specializing in backpacking and hiking in Lapland. Tunturilatu ry is also a member organization of the Suomen Latu, which was established in 1938 to promote sports and physical activity of among the Finnish people.

Professori Lauri Pihkalan aloitteesta seuraavana vuonna 1955 järjestettiin ensimmäinen kaikille avoin Pirkan hiihto, 90 km mittainen laturetki, jossa oli retkihiihdon lisäksi myös kilpasarja. Pirkan hiihdossa haluttiin tarjota tilaisuus nimenomaan pitkän matkan hiihtovaellukseen.

http://data.europeana.eu/item/2021009/_2.description:
sisällön kuvaus: Participants of Pirkka ski race skiing in 1954. 15 members from Tunturilatu ry participated in the opening event of Pirkka ski track from Niinisalo to Tampere in 1954.    
  
The first public Pirkka ski race was organized one year later in 1955, after professor Lauri Pihkala`s proposition. He and other members of Tunturilatu ry wanted to increase the popularity of long distance ski touring.  The route of Pirkka ski race was 90 km long and there were hiking and racing series.    
  
Tunturilatu ry is a sport organization specializing in backpacking and hiking in Lapland. Tunturilatu ry is also a member organization of the Suomen Latu, which was established in 1938 to promote sports and physical activity of among the Finnish people.

http://data.europeana.eu/item/91616/arme.description:
Grupp M II.
Bronsmedalj till minne av Olympiska spelen i Stockholm 1912.

Åtsida: Zeus-bild, sittande på stol, profil vänster, höger hand utsträckt och däri stående Pallas Athena-bild, stolen placerad på en kolonn med joniskt kapitäl, i bakgrunden Stockholmsvy med Slottet, Norrbro och Riksdagshuset. Signering nedtill till vänster: "Erik Lindberg". Omskrift upptill: "Till minne af olympiska spelen Stockholm 1912".

Frånsida: Qvadriga åkande åt vänster, i vagnen en stående naken yngling med segerkrans, fladdrande mantel, i vänster hand en stor palmkvist som går ihop med mantelns veck, naken körsven med piska. På avsnitt nedtill till vänster signatur: "B M", till höger "Vaughtons Birm".

Paddel eller åra med nästan runt årblad. Den är synnerligan välarbetad och målad. Handtaget är svartmålat och snidat. Årbladet är likaså svartmålat ända in på skaftet och dessutom dekorerat med målade blomrankor i gult, grått och vitt. Mönstret är olika på bägge sidor. (generalkatalogen)

"gives af Indianerna i Pará såsom fredstecken". Denna form på årbladet tycks förekomma på själva Amuzonas, Se Whiffen, pl. XXX:5, samt högre upp ända till Huallaga, se Uhle, pl. 26:6. http://data.europeana.eu/item/2024904/ht.description:
This has been called the great ice-age . More and more shows are being put on ice and ice rinks are doing big business in all large cities . But the Roller - skating rinks , older institutions , are still going remarkably strong , and they are especially popular with children . The noise , as well as the speed , seems to appeal to them .  These pictures , taken at the Roller Skating Rink at Alexandra Palace in London ,capture the excitement and jollity of Saturday morning at the rink , with school over for the week , and the whole expanse of the hall waiting for experts and beginners , the whizzers and the stumblers .
PICTURE SHOWS:- A young woman skating
March 1955

http://data.europeana.eu/item/117/_508AA.description:
fyysinen kuvaus: Rullaluistin pari, metallia, kumipyörät, kuminen jarrupala sekä punaiset muoviset kiristimet - siteet, 2 kpl / luistin. Rullaluistinen runko metallia, terästä. Kaksi leveää jalkaa vasten tulevaa osaa, joiden etäisyyttä toisistaan mahdollista säätää  
pohjassa olevia ruuveja löysäämällä. Taaemman levyn takalaidassa ylöspäin nousevat kaarevat tuet, joiden lävitse muovinen ns. nilkkaremmi kulkee. Remmin solki metallia. Etummaiset soljet niin ikään punaista muovia, metalliset läpiviennit 6 kpl, joista pujotettu tummunut kengännyöri, jolla luistin tiukattu kenkään. Luistinten takaosassa metallinen hieman p-kirjainta muistuttava mustalla kumilla pinnoitettu jarrupala. Mustia kumirenkaita 4 kpl. Rullaluistinten renkaat lienevät olleen vaihdettavissa.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/117/_508AA.title: rullaluistimet
http://data.europeana.eu/item/117/_508AA.creator: Rake OY

http://data.europeana.eu/item/117/_09A1A.description:
fyysinen kuvaus: Kenkä mustaa muovia, vuori mustaa kangasta, joka vahvistettu vihreällä nailonkankaalla. Päällä kolme hammastettua kiristyslenkkiä. Kengän pohjaan kiinnitetty kisko, jossa neljä kumipäällysteistä pyörää. Jarrupala oikean kengän kiskossa (mahd. siirtää
  
vasempaan kiskoon).

http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.description:
As a young man, our father, T. P. "Tom" Murphy, of Limerick, Ireland, enjoyed playing team sports and was a member of CBS Limerick Senior Schools rugby team of 1932 and 1933. He rowed successfully with Limerick Boat Club. 

He later switched to track and field and was Munster Decathlon Champion on a number of occasions. His greatest talent was in the Pole Vault, where he harbored ambitions to represent Ireland in the Olympics. 

He won his first Irish Championship on 11 July 1937 when he cleared 11 feet (3.35 meters) at the National Athletic and Cycling Association in Killarney, Kerry. At that time in Ireland the landing pit was comprised of hessian sacks filled with straw unlike the deep foam pits today. Tom practiced in his long back garden where there was plenty of space to improve his skills. 

In 1938, he was the favourite to retain his title but unfortunately, his bamboo pole snapped while competing and the rules at the time did not allow him to borrow a pole to complete the competition. 

Poles at the time were made of bamboo or aluminium. Modern pole-vaulters since the 1950s used a flexible fibreglass pole which enabled them to reach much higher heights. On 16 July 1939, in Thurles, Tipperary, Tom regained the Irish Pole Vault Championship Title, this time clearing a height of 11 feet and 3 inches (3.43 metres). This Irish record was unbeaten until 1955. 

Due to the outbreak of World War II, his dreams of representing Ireland at the Olympic Games were never realised. 

Tom was our unassuming father, who seldom spoke of his achievements but whose enthusiasm and knowledge of athletics informed and enhanced our enjoyment of Irish, European and Olympic sports as we watched them with Tom on the television growing up in Limerick.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.title: Pole vaulting from the back garden into the Irish record books

http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.description:
The oldest thing I have brought along from my collection is this schools club match photo from the Irish Times. It was taken in 1960. This was my first major match; I was under 14 and it was an U15 match. I played in the back row with my school, Gonzaga, against our rivals, Mountjoy. Two of my team mates pictured here went on to have successful rugby careers; Barry Bresland went on to play for the British & Irish Lions and Joe Davy, who went on to become a well-known rugby international. 

Not long afterwards I moved school to Clongowes in Kildare but I didn't make it on to their team as I was smaller than the other players. I started college in 1963 and initially studied commerce before transferring to the law school. Soon after I began studying at UCD, I selected for the university rugby team. For the 1966/67 term I became team secretary and received this blue honours scarf. I’ve also brought along three of my membership books from my time in UCD, which list all the club officials, players and fixtures for each season. 

After graduating from UCD I joined Palmerstown Rugby Club in 1968-69. In those days I was in the 3rd A’s team and in 1970 I went on to become captain of the team. During my tenure as captain we played 5 matches, got to the league semi-final and lost in the replay. My playing career came to an end when I was 28 when I injured my back and had to stop competing.
The club itself was established in 1899, to give Church of Ireland (Anglican) gentleman exercise in the evening. It was roughly 50/50 Catholic and Protestant but religion was never an issue. A friend of mine convinced me to join, and I still have many friends from my time there. When we moved the club to new grounds in 197X many of the players didn’t follow and the club eventually folded and merged with De La Salle to become De La Salle/Palmerstown in 1978. This rugby ball was the last ball used before the Palmerstown moved to its new club grounds. It's signed by some of the players who played that day and is one of my most treasured possessions. Another object I’ve brought along is my green and black Palmerstown scarf. Sadly, these days I only get to use it at funerals. 
________________

Around 1969 we worked in the Post Office. Went to Scotland to see them play Ireland. My mother and sister made the shirts. 

We thought we could go onto the field before the match but the police said we were not allowed. We then decided to go out again as the Irish side came out before kick-off. Not everyone came out on the pitch. We were running around the pitch, I got called over by a policeman and got arrested and spent the night in jail. A friend of mine was also arrested and charged with resisting arrest. Another man, separate from our group, had annoyed the police and was arrested as well. 

A friend whose father was the president of the IRFU spoke to contact and arranged for them to be released. We were let out on bail but while there was representation for the other two men, there was no representation for me, so there was an arrest warrant issued for me. The solicitor cleared it up a few days later. Match occurred in February 1965 Scotland vs Ireland, Ireland won but I didn't get to see any of it. 

It was a defining moment for me as I felt it was all handle wrong at the time, so I moved from Commerce to Law and became a solicitor. 

Bill Mulcahy was the Irish captain that day and heard about the arrest and said they would take it out on the Scots, which they did.
_____________________________________

Among other things I have a large collection of match programmes, over 120, if not more, mostly Munster Rugby. When I finished working in 2010 and I approached the IRFU about the idea of a rugby museum in Dublin. It got a bit of traction but unfortunately it never got off the ground. 

I would still love to see one opened and remain hopeful that it might still materialise.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.title: My passion for Irish Rugby

http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.description:
I have lots of memorabilia belonging to my late Uncle Tom Cleary -arguably the greatest scrum half never to have gained a cap for Ireland. My book ‘Suitcase Number Seven-a rugby story with a difference’ tells his story. A sub up to 17 times on the Irish team, he never gained the distinction of a cap. 
All his treasured possessions, programmes, match reports, menus, photos and boots were found after his death in the suitcase he was allocated for Ireland’s tour to South Africa and Rhodesia in May 1961. There are lots of photos of said memorabilia in the book.
His story is about natural talent in the extreme, allied to a competitive nature and leadership ability. But, blow by blow, life chipped away at his gifts to reveal an intensely low self esteem. It took a huge life crisis for Tom to realise and accept that he was truly loved … just for being himself.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.title: Tom Cleary & his Suitcase Number Seven
