http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.description:
Having been lucky enough to play professional rugby for six years, I have many happy moments to look back on (as well as plenty of challenging ones). 

Naturally, when looking back at occasions that stand out, someone's professional debut is usually the first that springs to mind. I am no different in that sense. It's rare that a player's first time is running onto the pitch wearing a Munster jersey in front of 26,000 people against a French side in a European Cup game.

I was very lucky to experience such a day. It is a memory I will cherish for as long as I live.

That's not the most memorable moment I had though. 

That came ten months later, once again in Thomond Park, once again in front of 26,000 people in the European Cup. It was my first European start in front of a home crowd. We convincingly beat a star-studded Saracens side in a performance that didn't get too much wrong. 

The game, the result, all of it was fantastic, but the memory I have is literally a few seconds long. It is still something that makes the hairs on the back of my neck stand up when I indulge myself enough to daydream about it in detail.

The preparation was done. We were all ready. We had come out of the tunnel to a roaring crowd, sized up the opposition from the half-way line and got into position in preparation for the referee's whistle. 

And that was the moment. I can feel the chills coming now as I write this. 

There was a period of about three or four seconds prior to kick-off where the crowd burst into life. We all know what crowd noise feels like; that's nothing new. But I can't articulate the noise that a full house in Thomond Park makes when virtually every supporter in the stadium is screaming at the top of their lungs.

As rugby players, we learn to focus on the task at hand. It's not healthy to be preoccupied with what is going on around you. On occasion, however, you get tiny little windows like this to appreciate just how lucky you are, and just how big an occasion you are part of. 

I remember very clearly, and always will, glancing around at the various stands, soaking up the noise with a smile, and thinking: "This is what it's all about. This is what they talk about."
http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.title: My first European Cup start

http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.description:
Torre del Greco è sempre stata una città fortemente orientata al calcio. Eppure possiamo vantare una nobile tradizione per quanto concerne il rugby.

La Polisportiva Turris, sezione Rugby, è nata negli anni ‘60 per volere di Alberto Ferrara. 

Per l’epoca si trattava di una novità, almeno in Campania, essendo la quarta squadra più antica della regione, fondata un anno prima anche del Benevento, che ha gareggiato ai massimi livelli per diverso tempo.

Il primo anno la formazione era composta da soli 18 elementi, il minimo necessario per partecipare alle gare, ed erano tutti giovanissimi. Ma già nella seconda stagione venne creata una squadra di riserve, incrementando sempre di più, col passare del tempo, il numero dei tesserati. 

Quelli furono anni “romantici”, in cui non esitavamo a prendere a nolo un pulmino delle suore pur di arrivare a sfidare il CUS Roma, una delle formazioni più rilevanti in ambito nazionale.

Con l’inizio degli anni settanta iniziammo ad essere più strutturati, cambiando anche il nome in Lions di Torre del Greco. Avevamo un buon numero di squadre e una sezione di minirugby dedicata ai giovani che si volevano avvicinare a questo sport. Tra l’altro, abbiamo annoverato tra le nostre fila anche il noto attore Lello Arena. 

Alla metà degli anni ottanta, dopo aver vinto il campionato regionale ed esserci iscritti a quello nazionale, abbiamo sfiorato anche una storica promozione in serie B. Comunque  non sono mancate anche altre soddisfazioni, con alcuni giovani convocati nella Nazionale giovanile. 

Con l’inizio del nuovo millennio abbiamo anche disputato il campionato di serie B, potendo usufruire del Liguori, il “tempio” del calcio a Torre del Greco. Dal 2013, purtroppo, lo stadio comunale non è stato più reso disponibile e abbiamo dovuto così emigrare a Boscotrecase, dove abbiamo avuto in gestione il campo che ha ospitato, tra l’altro, le Universiadi del 2019.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.title: Breve storia del rugby a Torre del Greco

Undersidan har haft tryckt mönster med stiliserade stjärnor. Truckar gjutna i lättmetall, märkta  venture. 4 hjul av syntetmaterial. Påklistrade klistermärken, 3 st. Relativt nött underdel, kanter och truckar. Har tillhört Tobias Janius i Trosa.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/916123/SLM.title: Tobias Janius skateboard från början av 2000-talet

http://data.europeana.eu/item/916123/SLM.description:
Skateboard med däck av vit hårdplast. Ovansidan täckt med plastimpregnerad väv, färgad gul och märkt "Skate Board". Bilder av flygplan i blått. Undersidan av samma material som ovansidan, målad vit. 5 klistermärken på undersidan, bland annat ICA KNUTEN, AG bil och Nugget Jeans. Truckar gjutna i lättmetall och märkta "S". 4 hjul av gummi. Nött.

Givaren berättade att puck påsattes mot slitage av bräda i "tailen" (bak), av åkarna själva. Gav svarta streck i asfalten vilket ansågs väldigt häftigt. meddelades i samband med att givaren besökte utställningen "Apropå 70-tal" i husvagnen år 2005.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/916123/SLM.title: Svens skateboard från 1970-talet

http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.description:
Het voelt heel onwennig dat ik net de Sport Penning 2021 heb gewonnen. Meestal ben ik degene die andere mensen in het zonnetje en nu is het mijn beurt met het Zeeburg Skate Park. 

Ik kan me het moment nog heel goed herinneren dat het skaten mij in zijn greep kreeg. Ik zat als jongen op honkbal en ik was super fanatiek. Ik vond skaten er altijd wel gaaf uitzien, maar ik had het zelf nog nooit geprobeerd. Tot dat ik naar de middelbare school ging en een vriendje leerde kennen. Samen met zijn vrienden hadden ze hout gejat uit de bouw en er een ramp van gemaakt. Het was waarschijnlijk één bak ellende, maar ik was erg onder de indruk. Niet alleen van de ramp, maar ook van het feit dat ze hun eigen cultuur leken te hebben en een eigen taal spraken. Ik heb toen heel veel auto’s moeten wassen en andere karweitjes gedaan en toen kon ik uiteindelijk mijn eigen board kunnen kopen. En ik ben sindsdien nooit meer gestopt met skaten. 

Skaten is niet voor iedereen, maar iedereen mag het proberen. In het begin is het eventjes leuk en dan ga je op je bek. Skaten is nou eenmaal niet makkelijk of logisch. Het gaat met vallen en opstaan en daardoor wordt al snel het kaf van het koren gescheiden. Als je een keer een blessure oploopt, ga je dan door of haak je af? Het gaat ook wel echt om je eigen grenzen opzoeken. Maar het gaat vooral om een leuke middag met elkaar hebben en elkaar ondersteunen, ook al lig je mijlenver uit elkaar qua techniek.  

Voor het Zeeburg Skate Park heb ik veel gelobbyd bij de gemeente Amsterdam. Het is een super mooie openbare voorziening voor skaten, BMX en steppen geworden. Het park was altijd een droom van mij en nu het ook daadwerkelijk is gerealiseerd, zie ik dat anderen er kennelijk ook behoefte aan hadden. Dat merk je door de enorme toestroom aan mensen die er naar toe gaan. Ik hoop dus dat er meer voorzieningen komen, ook elders in de stad. Niet alleen om de druk van Zeeburg te halen, maar het is gewoon leuk om te zien hoe jong en oud samenkomen. Bovendien is het ook leuk om als voorbijganger gewoon even naar te kijken. 

--
Het hele interview met Stan kun je hier bekijken: https://vimeo.com/683306685 en op het vimeo-account van Europeana: https://vimeo.com/europeana
http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.title: Stan Postmus: Winnaar Sport Penning 2021

http://data.europeana.eu/item/916124/S_X.description:
Måsbergsbacken, hoppremiär. Arbetarbladet. 18 februari 1951.
Ny publicering. Namn och nytt, Arbetarbladet 12 februari 2005.
Redaktör Siv Berg. På 1950- och 60 talet var backhoppning en stor sport i vårt land, men Gävle hade ingen bra backe. Det hade tidigare funnits en oanvändbar backe vid Gustafsbro och en i Hemlingby. För att ge extra skjuts åt sporten beslutade Gävle skidklubb att bygga en hoppbacke på Måsberget på Brynäs. - Det var Ture Edbom, kommunalråd och backhoppare som tyckte vi borde fixa en backe. Han, jag och ett gäng från Sundsvall byggde backen tillsammans och den invigdes 18 februari 1951. Det berättar gamle backhopparräven Erik Magnusson, 80 år, Gävle, som suttit med i Skidförbundets backhoppningskommitté i 30 år och varit bisittare till Sven "Plex" Pettersson i tv i 25 år. Vid invigningen av nya Måsbergsbacken rådde våldsamt yrväder, men Erik gjorde ändå ett långt och stilfullt premiärhopp på 29 meter och kom fyra i tävlingen. Vann gjorde regerande juniormästaren Lasse Schyberger. Vid ett senare tilfälle satt Erik backrekord på 41,5 meter. Måsbergsbackens öde beseglades år 1967. - Då blåste backen omkull i en snöstorm. Backen var stadgad med vajrar, men de räckte inte till när det blåste hård nordan, berättar Erik.

Backen var stadgad med vajrar, men de räckte inte till när det blåste hård nordan, berättar Erik.

Ny publicering. Namn och nytt, Arbetarbladet 12 februari 2005.
Redaktör Siv Berg. På 1950- och 60 talet var backhoppning en stor sport i vårt land, men Gävle hade ingen bra backe. Det hade tidigare funnits en oanvändbar backe vid Gustafsbro och en i Hemlingby. http://data.europeana.eu/item/2024904/ht.description:
Eddy Swan , a young amateur parachutist , with his electric parachute gear , intends to jump out of the old year into the new year at Broxbourne Aerodrome . It will be only the third time that a night parachute descent has been made deliberately in Britain . It will also be the first test of a novel lighting device which it is hoped will make descents in the darkness as safe as those in daylight . Mr Swan will wear a flying suit to which are affixed a number of electric lamps . These are intended to guide the parachutist to a safe landing . He will make his leap into space at 11. 58 pm and try to land in the centre of the aerodrome during the first one or two minutes of 1934 . Mr Swan is to make an attempt on world ' s record night parachute jump ._x000D_
Photo shows ;  Mr Eddy Swan in his electric parachute gear . He generates his own electricity for the illumination ._x000D_
31 December 1933

http://data.europeana.eu/item/2022042/10.title: Neljä aikuista laskee puurakenteisella kelkalla mäkeä Helsingin Kaivopuistossa. Edellä juoksee koira, joka näyttää lähinnä suomenpystykorvalta. Mäki on jyrkkä ja lasku juuri alkamassa, vauhdin hurma ja yhteisen tekemisen ilo paistavat kasvoilta. Miehet istuvat kelkassa edessä ja naiset selän takana. Yksi mies on vielä perää pitämässä kelkan jalasten kannoilla. Kuvateksti Suomen Sosialidemokraatissa: Laskiaisiloa Kaivopuistossa.

http://data.europeana.eu/item/951/Cultur.description: Medalie, "Sportul", gravor Marie Alexandre-Lucien Coudray (1864 – 1932). Avers: o scenă alegorică, o zeitate ( Atena/Nike?), privește și arată cu mâna către dreaptă. Lângă ea, un bărbat cu privirea către dreapta. Zeița este înfățișată cu coif și ramură de lauri în mâna dreaptă. Pe fundal, un câmp arat(?), copaci și în partea dreaptă jos, lauri, un coif și o sabie. În exergă, numele gravorului L. COUDRAY Revers: o compoziție alegorică cu diferite simboluri ale sportului. În partea dreaptă o bicicletă, puști, desupra soarele răsărind. În partea stângă, trei ținte. Dedesubt, mai multe obiecte simbol: o tobă, o trompetă, o sabie, o rachetă de tenis, o ancoră etc. Peste acestea, o placă dreptunghiulară (lăsată liberă pentru gravare). Dedesubt, un porumbel. În partea stângă, inscripția medalistului LC.

http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.description:
Surfing arrived in Ireland in 1949 when fourteen year old Joe Roddy took to the water on his homemade four metre paddle board near Dundalk. 

Joe's board was inspired by an article he read about the Hawaiian "Sport Of Kings" in a Readers Digest.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.title: Ireland's First Surfer, Joe Roddy, Dundalk, 1949

http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.description:
The first Irish National Surfing Championships were held in Tramore, Co Waterford in 1967 following the establishment of the Surf Club Of Ireland in 1966. The Surf Club of Ireland, which later became Irish Surfing, the National Governing Body of Surfing today, was initiated by Bray man, Kevin Cavey. 

In 1966, Kevin received an invitation to compete at the World Surfing Championships in San Diego. When he returned from the Championships the club members were excited to hear how the event had gone. Kevin outlined how the contest was run, sowing the seeds for a decision to host the first Irish National Surfing Championships in Tramore in September 1967.

Kevin Cavey won the contest taking the first Irish National Surfing Title. He was joined in the final by Eammon Matthews, Roger Steadman and Martin Lloyd. In 1981 Grace O'Sullivan was the first Irish Women's Surfing Champion to be crowned.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.title: First Irish National Surfing Championships

http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.description:
In 1966 the Surf Club Of Ireland was formed, a club that later became Irish Surfing, the National Governing Body of Surfing today.

The club was the result of a chain of events initiated by Bray man, Kevin Cavey. Kevin discovered surfing in 1962, when he saw a picture of a Hawaiian surfer in a Reader’s Digest. This picture was his inspiration for a life-long passion for surfing. 

For the next few years, Kevin experimented with making his own boards, connecting with other surfers and forming Ireland’s first Surf Club. 

In 1966, Kevin decided it was time to tell Ireland that surfing had arrived. He took a stand at the Boat Show, titled Bray Ireland Surf Club, and was inundated with interest.

Following the success of the Boat Show, Kevin, who had just received delivery of his first custom fibreglass surfboard, his brother Colm, Tom Casey and Patrick Kinsella set off on their first great Surfari in a Vauxhall Victor 101 station wagon with a stack of surfboards on the roof. Their great surfari marked the bringing of surfing to the West. 

Their first stop was Strandhill, Co Sligo followed by Rossnowlagh, Co Donegal and then North to the Causeway Coast.

On returning home from the Surfari, the Surf Club Of Ireland was formed, a club representing all Ireland. By the late 1960s surfing was expanding rapidly and regional clubs began to emerge including North Coast Surf Club, West Coast Surf Club, South Coast Surf Club, Rossnowlagh Surf Club and Fastnet Surf Club. 

At this point, the Surf Club Of Ireland became the Irish Surfing Association, the National Governing Body linking the newly emerged clubs.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.title: Irish Surfing Is Born

http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.description:
Irish Surfing has hosted Eurosurf, the biannual European Surfing Championships on four occasions: 

1972, Lahinch, Co Clare
1985, Rossnowlagh, Co Donegal
1997 & 2011, Bundoran, Co Donegal
http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.title: Ireland Hosts Eurosurf

http://data.europeana.eu/item/2084002/co.description:
My story begins in England. That is where my parents are from. We were on holiday at a beach called Broadstairs. There were a lot of surfers there and they inspired me a lot which made me want a surfboard so I bought one. My new surfboard is green and black, bumpy and easy to surf on. I like surfing in the winter because the waves are bigger waves and my board goes faster and further.                                                                      

Now we live in Holland and I go to surf the giant surf off Hart beach. Both my brother and I go surfing together.  One day, I want to go back to Broadstairs beach with my surfboard. Maybe I will even live in England one day.                                                                                                                                   

--- 

This story was contributed by a pupil of The British School in The Netherlands.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/2084002/co.title: Surfing with my brother

http://data.europeana.eu/item/92085/1788.description:
Kopš 18. gadsimta beigām Baldone pazīstama kā kūrorts. 1796. gadā Baldonē tiek ierīkota sēravota dziednīca. Kūrorta nozīme gan mazinājās pēc Ķemeru kūrorta atklāšanas 1838. gadā. Padomju Latvijas laikos Baldones kūrorts bija ļoti populāra atpūtas un ārsniecības vieta visā Padomju Savienībā. Baldones kūrorts tiek uzskatīts par vecāko Baltijā un 19. gadsimta sākumā bija viens no ievērojamākajiem Krievijā. Šobrīd minerālavoti netiek izmantoti, bet sanatorijas apbūvei nepieciešama nopietna restaurācija un pārbūve.
Baldones sanatorijā bija iekārtots lielākais atklātais peldbaseins Latvijā. To atjaunoja sanatorijas parkā pēc Otrā pasaules kara. Peldbaseins bija 400 kvadrātmetrus liels un 1,0 līdz 2,4 metrus dziļš. Piecus metrus augstā tramplīna tuvumā dziļums – 4,0 metri. Bērniem domātajā peldbaseina daļā ūdens dziļums nepārsniedz 80 centrimetrus. Peldbaseina tuvumā iekārtotas kabīnes drēbju novietošanai, soliņi. Peldbaseins vēl darbojās 20. gadsimta 60.70. gados. Koka ēkas arī tajā laikā jau bija sliktā stāvoklī. Šobrīd vieta izpostīta
http://data.europeana.eu/item/92085/1788.title: Baldone. Brīvdabas peldētava

http://data.europeana.eu/item/318/marc_n.description: Up to the middle of June the weather in Israel has been for the most part almost idyllic, warm pleasant summer days and cool evenings, Suddenly summer is here, as if overnight, Hot humid days and little relief at night as Israelis prepare to sweat it out for the next twelve weeks, Apart from the odd days when the hot dry 'sharav' winds caused the temperature to soar, the real summer heat has been late in coming. This phenomena, which nobody complains about, is perhaps another indication of the possible change in the world's climate, It is now, with the real summer heat, that Israel's water problem will be more apparent, With water stocks depleted and natural evaporation of lakes and reservoirs during the hot months, the situation will be critical if there is another 'dry' winter this year, With a sudden rise in temperatures, the only sensible place to be is in the sea; Photo shows: The picture shows a young bather on the Tel-Aviv beach today.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/318/marc_n.title: PHEW! SUMMER IS HERE.

http://data.europeana.eu/item/318/marc_n.description: Israel has always been a centre of fashion and design. Her clothing manufacturing industry supplies shops all over the world. The 'Made in Israel' label seen in many large chain stores in Europe and the US has become a by-word for quality. One particular side of the fashion industry that has been an Israeli speciality is swimwear. All the large firms have shown or are shooing the designs that will be seen on the world's beaches in the summer. Photo shows: The picture shows models showng some of the new swimwear by Pilpel.

http://data.europeana.eu/item/92085/2361.description: Liepāja, tenisa laukums Jūrmalas parkā 20. gadsimta 20. gados. 1895. gadā Liepājas pilsētas valde pieņēma lēmumu izveidot parku starp Peldu un Krasta (tag. Liepu) ielām pēc Rīgas galvenā dārznieka G. Kufalta (Kuphaldt) projekta. Līdz 1906. gadam turpinājās grūts darbs - bija jāuzved auglīgā zeme un jāsagādā stādāmie koki un krūmi. Apstādījumos tika izvietoti vairāki tenisa laukumi, bet parka dienvidu daļā - sporta laukums. Liepājas Jūrmalas parks bija Latvijā lielākais - tas stiepās 3 km gar Liepājas pludmali (šobrīd tas aizņem 70 hektārus un ir uzskatāms par vienu no lielākajiem Latvijā). Mūsdienās parks ir ieguvis vietējas nozīmes dendroloģiska stādījuma statusu
http://data.europeana.eu/item/92085/2361.title: Liepāja. Tenisa laukums Jūrmalas parkā

http://data.europeana.eu/item/621/BJC185.title: Sportive ale Liceului de fete „Regina Maria” din Cluj înainte sau după o partidă de dublu la tenis în parcul „Victor Babeș” (actualmente Parcul Sportiv „Iuliu Hațieganu”)

http://data.europeana.eu/item/621/BJC185.description: Vaida Gavrilă a avut o bogată activitate sportivă, secția de tenis condusă de Vaida Gavrilă fiind una din cele mai bune școli de tenis de câmp din țară. De aici au pornit în viața sportivă nume mari ale tenisului românesc: Virginia Ruzici, Ionel Santeiu și Petru Santeiu. Primii tenismeni formați de el au ajuuns la „Universitatea” Cluj, apoi la cluburi din țară: Târgu Mureș, Oradea, Arad și Brașov. Primii care au ajuns la București au fost Sever Mureșan, Ionel Santeiu, Letiția Man, Ilie Giurgiu, Mihai Stoleru, Doina Sîrbu și Lucian Boldor. Președintele Federației Române de Tenis, marele campion Gogu Viziru, văzând rezultatele excelente, a trimis la Câmpia Turzii primele rachete Dunlop și Slazenger și mingi Dunlop, iar pe cei mai buni tenismeni antrenați de Vaida i-a invitat în 1961-1964 în tabere de tenis la București și Cluj. Rod al antrenamentului și a pregătirii serioase, dar și al talentului, în 1965, ISCT a promovat în prima ligă de tenis, cu o echipă din care niciunul nu trecea de 17 ani: Ionel Santeiu, Sever Mureșan, Lucian Boldor, Emil Stan, Ilie Giurgiu, Doina Sîrbu. În 1966, echipa a jucat acasă cu Dinamo București, un titan al vremurilor, cu Ion Țiriac și Sever Dron în echipă. Apoi cu alt titan, clubul Steaua, care îi avea în echipă pe Ilie și Costică Năstase și pe Petre Mărmureanu. Jucătorii formați de Vaida Gavrilă au fost atât de buni, încât pe Sever Mureșan și pe Ionel Santeiu i-a și luat Dinamo, Lucian Boldor și Ilie Giurgiu au plecat la Poli Cluj, iar Letiția Man la Steaua. La începutul anilor 70 și Virginia Ruzici avea să plece la clubul Dinamo, unde a fost antrenată de Aurel Segărceanu.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/621/BJC185.title: Vaida Gavrila, trainer of tennis players from Turzii Plain, the first coach of Virginia Ruzici
http://data.europeana.eu/item/621/BJC185.creator: Arion, Ion

http://data.europeana.eu/item/621/BJC185.description: Virginia Ruzici (born January 31, 1955, Turzii Plain, Cluj County) is the first tennis player in our country to win a Grand Slem tournament (1978). From the grounds of “Colonia Maria,” the training and training place of the tennis players from the Turzii Plain, Virginia stepped by step the road to Roland-Garros. Virginia is the daughter of an acclaimed footballer from the Turzii Plain, where he launched, at the former Division B Arieşul Turda winner of a Romanian Cup edition and who would reach the title of one of the most titled football teams from Romania in the interwar period, FC Rapid. Virginia Ruzici is one of the 7 tennis players in the world who had managed to qualify in all 3 finals existing in a Grand Prix tournament: in singles, doubles and mixed doubles, in 1978, in Roland-Garros, prevailing in the top 2. Playing in the quarter-finals at the Australian Open (1980), Wimbledon (1978 and 1981) and the US Open (1976 and 1978), she recorded 14 wins in singles, 11 times she was in singles finals, 7 times she won doubles titles, 9 times she was in doubles finals and twice she reached doubles mixed finals. There is no record in Romanian women’s tennis that equals it. He retired from his sports career in 1987. After the end of his career, until 1993, he worked for IMG-Mc Cormack, as manager, dealing mainly with players Monica Seles, Mary Pierce and Aranta Sanchez. Then he went on television making cometaries for various channels. He worked for “Eurosport” in France, then for “Pathe Sport,” a time for “Paris Première” in English, but also for the Australian channel “Channel 7.”

http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.description:
CS Politehnica Cluj s-a înfiinţat în anul 2009 prin Ordinul Ministrului Educatiei, Cercetarii si Inovarii datorită rezultatelor internaţionale de excepţie obţinute în special de secţiile de Karate și aeromodelism. CS Politehnica Cluj a început activitatea cu patru secții: aeromodelism, bridge, polo pe apă și karate WKC.

Până în prezent, în cadrul clubului există 10 secții: karate WUKF, aeromodelism, bridge, polo pe apă, tenis de masă, cu doua echipe, masculin si feminine, kempo, oină, triathlon, natație, ciclism. Secţia Karate este cu siguranţă secţia care a adus clubului cele mai multe trofee naționale și internaţionale, în anii de activitate, atât la cadeţi cât și la juniori și seniori.
În scurta istorie a clubului, care dorește să renască valorile sportive universitare ale Clujului, se pot menţiona titluri de campioni naţionali, europeni sau mondiali obţinute de sportivii clubului, laureaţi ai celor mai prestigioase clasamente sportive în România, dar și din străinătate. 

Clubul isi propune sa organizeze competiţii naţionale și internaţionale la Cluj-Napoca pentru a face cunoscut numele de POLITEHNICA și implicit numele Universităţii Tehnice.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.title: Din activitatea secției de triathlon a CS Politehnica Cluj

http://data.europeana.eu/item/951/Cultur.description: Copie după medalia dedicată scufundării vasului britanic "RMS Lusitania". Avers: o compoziție simbolică - un grup de oameni stând la coadă la un ghișeu unde morții (reprezentați prin schelete umane) vând bilete. În partea stângă, un bărbat citește un ziar cu inscripția, "U Boo[t]/ Gefah[r]?". Sus, legenda, "GESCHAFT UBER ALLES". În exergă, inițialele "K.G", (Karl Goetz, gravorul medaliei originale). Revers: vasul RMS Lusitania scunfundându-se în apele mării. În partea superioară, inscripția în formă de arc, "KEINE BANN WARE"; în exergă, legenda "DER GROSSDAMPFER/ = LUSITANIA =/ DURCH EIN DEUTSCHES/ TAUCHBOOT VERSENKT/ 5 MAI 1915". Medalia originală a fost bătută în Germania pentru a comemora scufundarea pachebotului RMS Lusitania de către un vas de război german. Acest tragic eveniment a influențat întrarea în primul război mondial a Statelor Unite ale Americii de partea Marii Britanii (între cele 1198 de victime se aflau și 128 de cetățeni americani). Medalia se păstrează în cutia originală.

http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.description:
It was the best of times! It really was! Sister Fidelis brought the game of volleyball to Patrician-Presentation Secondary School, Fethard in 1970 and we just loved it! 

Quote from The Nationalist (newspaper) on December 26 ,1970: Volleyball was played competitively for the first time ever in Fethard on Thursday of last week when Presentation Convent, Thurles played Fethard Presentation Convent in senior and junior matches. Thurles won both games, though the Fethard girls gave a great display considering the short time they are playing the game.

We practiced every evening with Sister Fidelis coaching and Sister Annunciata encouraging, which culminated in our winning the All Ireland Final at Senior and Cadet level in 1974, thereby qualifying for the FISEC international games in Zaragoza, Spain that Easter.

Busloads travelled to Cork that day where we beat Eccles Street, Dublin, our big rivals of the previous few years. (I have a poor memory, but I still remember that their star player was called Wanda Knopek!) Glory days!  

There was such pride and joy in the school and in the community, who supported us so well. I can still remember the excitement in the lead up to Easter, for what was (for most of us) our first trip abroad. My memories of the actual trip are dim now but I know we had a great time, whatever about our success on the court! I imagine we had Y Viva Espana ('Oh, this year I’m off to sunny Spain...') sung to death by the time we returned to Ireland!

Subsequently, in 1975 the cadet team won the All Ireland and played very well in the FISEC games in Louvain, Belgium.

The school was successful again in 1978 when the senior team represented Ireland in Leeds.

There were lots of other great teams and national wins over the years and so many young girls who benefitted hugely from this sport.

Sister Fidelis still returns to Fethard sporadically for special events. I’m sure she must have a sense of pride in the new life, energy and skill she introduced to the pupils of the 70s and 80s. It was such an important part of our secondary education.  Sister Annunciata, R.I.P., will be remembered by the players for her enthusiasm, support and her dedication to the cause.

It is good to know that the tradition of volleyball lives on in Patrician-Presentation Fethard and that the teams of girls and boys under various coaches still achieve great success.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.title: Volleyball Comes to Fethard

http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.description:
Colecție personală de fotografii Demostene Șofron  

Colecția cuprinde imagini cu voleibaliști români, jucători și antrenori la cluburile locale, campioni naționali și intenaționali.

Demostene Șofron este jurnalist și comentator sportiv din 1990. Este absolvent al Facultății de Litere (1986) și al Facultății de Educație Fizică și Sport (2000). A fost arbitru divizionar de volei (1977-2013), arbitru de tenis de masă (2014 - în prezent), arbitru de automobilism carting moto (1987- în prezent). Redactor sportiv la cotidianul „Făclia de Cluj” din 1984 până în prezent.

http://data.europeana.eu/item/2022042/10.title: Kuvassa Kiljavan opiston toisen vuosikurssin opiskelijoita pelaamassa lentopalloa.
Kuvassa meneillään Työväen Akatemian ja Sirola-opiston naisopiskelijoiden välinen lentopallo-ottelu. Taustalla näkyy Vanajanlinna.
SNK:n urheilukilpailut Valkeakoskella 28-29.7.1979. Kuvassa lentopallon peluuta.
Säkylän retkeilypäiviltä, lentopalloa. Kuva Nuorin siivin lehdessä 7/1962.
Heinolan "Lentopallokonkarit" retkeilypäivillä Valkeakoskella.
Kuvassa Työväen Akatemian lentopallojoukkue Sirola-opistolla vuonna 1953. Keskellä, neljäntenä vasemmalta lukien, kuvan lahjoittaja Kalevi Pihanurmi.
Kuvassa oikealla Antti Kalliomäki tuomitsi lentopalloa ja vasemmalla Veikko Kiljunen.
Kuvan takana teksti: "Kolmen kovan koitos. Sirola-opiston opiskelijat pelaamassa lentopalloa".

http://data.europeana.eu/item/847/RIM_it.description:
Blå badmössa med nr 5 använd av Arne Jutner i klubblaget Hellas och i landslaget i vattenpolo. 

Arne Jutner (1920-2009) deltog i olympiska spelen i London 1948 (femte plats) och i Helsingfors 1952 (nionde plats). Han tillhörde klubbarna SoIK Hellas, Stockholm 1948 och Stockholmspolisens IF 1952.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/847/RIM_it.title: Meeting

http://data.europeana.eu/item/847/RIM_it.description:
Diplom från de olympiska spelen i Antwerpen 1920. Text: "VII Olympiade Anvers 1920, 3e prix Water polo, Torsten Kumfeldt, Suede".

Torsten Kumfeldt (1886-1966) var en svensk simmare och målvakt i vattenpolo. Tävlade för Stockholms KK. Har vunnit bronsmedalj i OS 1908 i London, silvermedalj i OS 1912 i Stockholm, bronsmedalj i OS 1920 i Antwerpen . Vann även sju SM i vattenpolo.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/847/RIM_it.title: Diplom

http://data.europeana.eu/item/847/RIM_it.description: Yellow swim cap with the Swedish flag. With white laces to tie under his chin. Use in swimming training in water polo 1948 at the Olympic Games in London, UK.

http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.description:
CS Politehnica Cluj s-a înfiinţat în anul 2009 prin Ordinul Ministrului Educatiei, Cercetarii si Inovarii datorită rezultatelor internaţionale de excepţie obţinute în special de secţiile de Karate și aeromodelism. CS Politehnica Cluj a început activitatea cu patru secții: aeromodelism, bridge, polo pe apă și karate WKC.

Până în prezent, în cadrul clubului există 10 secții: karate WUKF, aeromodelism, bridge, polo pe apă, tenis de masă, cu doua echipe, masculin si feminine, kempo, oină, triathlon, natație, ciclism. Secţia Karate este cu siguranţă secţia care a adus clubului cele mai multe trofee naționale și internaţionale, în anii de activitate, atât la cadeţi cât și la juniori și seniori.
În scurta istorie a clubului, care dorește să renască valorile sportive universitare ale Clujului, se pot menţiona titluri de campioni naţionali, europeni sau mondiali obţinute de sportivii clubului, laureaţi ai celor mai prestigioase clasamente sportive în România, dar și din străinătate. 

Clubul isi propune sa organizeze competiţii naţionale și internaţionale la Cluj-Napoca pentru a face cunoscut numele de POLITEHNICA și implicit numele Universităţii Tehnice.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/256/contri.title: Din activitatea secției de polo a CS Politehnica Cluj

http://data.europeana.eu/item/2021648/re.description: Een Olympisch winnaarsdiploma van de Olympische Zomerspelen 1948 Londen. Bovenaan het diploma staat de zwarte inscriptie ‘OLYMPIC GAMES LONDON’. In het midden staat een lauwerkrans weergegeven waarin de zwarte inscriptie staat ‘DIPLOMA’met daaronder de Olympische Ringen en daaronder ‘R.F. van Feggelen / HOLLAND / Swimming 3rd WaterPolo’ Het diploma is ondertekend door president van de Spelen, chairman van het Organisatorisch Comité en president van het IOC. Aan weerszijde van de krans zijn twee palmtakken weergegeven en onderaan het jaartal 1948.

http://data.europeana.eu/item/2021648/re.description: Een deelnemersspeld van de Olympische Zomerspelen 1924 Parijs. De schildvormige insigne toont bovenaan de gekleurde Olympische Ringen met daaronder een rode tekstbalk met de inscriptie 'CONCURRENT'. In het schild staat een schild met daarboven de inscriptie 'COF'. Aan de rand staat de inscriptie 'VIIIe OLYMPIADE PARIS 1924'. De speld was van Gerard Bohlander. Gérard (Gé) Bohlander (Amsterdam, 5 november 1895 – Kelpen, 18 december 1940) was een Nederlandse waterpolospeler. Gé Bohlander nam tweemaal deel aan de Olympische Spelen in 1920 en 1924. Hij eindigde met de nationale ploeg op respectievelijk de zevende (ex aequo) en de vijfde plaats.

http://data.europeana.eu/item/2021648/re.description: Medailles van de Olympische Zomerspelen 1924 Parijs en 1928 Amsterdam. Een insigne en een herinneringsmedaille van de Olympische Zomerspelen 1924 Parijs. De medaille toont op de voorzijde een gevleugelde vrouw in toga. die op een naakte atleet die rechts staat kroont met een lauwerkrans. Op de achterzijde staat bovenaan een stadaanzicht van Parijs met daaronder de inscriptie 'VIIIe OLYMPIADE / PARIS / 1924'. De schildvormige insigne toont bovenaan de gekleurde Olympische Ringen met daaronder een rode tekstbalk met de inscriptie 'CONCURRENT'. In het schild staat een schild met daarboven de inscriptie 'COF'. Aan de rand staat de inscriptie 'VIIIe OLYMPIADE PARIS 1924'. Een insigne en een herinneringsmedaille van de Olympische Zomerspelem 1928. Op de voorzijde van de medaille staan een man en een vrouw die samen een fakkel vasthouden. Op de achterzijde staat het Olympisch Stadium met in de rand de inscriptie 'IXe OLYMPIADE AMSTERDAM'. De ronde insigne heeft bovenaan de Nederlandse vlag, met daarin de inscriptie 'IXe / OLYMPIADE / AMSTERDAM'. Op de insigne staan de gekleurde Olympische Ringen met rondom de inscriptie '1928 / OFFICIEL'. De medailles waren van Gerard Bohlander. Gérard (Gé) Bohlander (Amsterdam, 5 november 1895 – Kelpen, 18 december 1940) was een Nederlandse waterpolospeler. Gé Bohlander nam tweemaal deel aan de Olympische Spelen in 1920 en 1924. Hij eindigde met de nationale ploeg op respectievelijk de zevende (ex aequo) en de vijfde plaats.

In het midden staat een lauwerkrans weergegeven waarin de zwarte inscriptie staat ‘DIPLOMA’ met daaronder de Olympische Ringen en daaronder 'HOLLAND / Swimming 3rd WaterPolo’ Het diploma is ondertekend door president van de Spelen, chairman van het Organisatorisch Comité en president van het IOC. Aan weerszijde van de krans zijn twee palmtakken weergegeven en onderaan het jaartal 1948.

http://data.europeana.eu/item/2021648/re.description: Lichtblauwe colbert van Piet Jan van der Giessen (1918-1993). Hij nam in 1952 deel aan de Olympische Spelen aan het onderdeel zeilen. Een lichtblauwe colbert met twee rijen knopen bestaande uit één knoop. De colbert heeft twee zakken en een linkerborstzakje met daarop een oranje applicatie in de vorm van een schild. Op de applicatie is bovenaan met goud geborduurd ‘NEDERLAND’ met daaronder het wapen van Nederland (de leeuw) en ‘1952’ met in het midden de gekleurde Olympische Ringen. Van der Giessen voer in de Internationale 5,5 meter klasse en behaalde samen met collegabemanningslid P.H. Keegstra de dertiende plaats. Vanaf 1962 was hij directeur van de scheepswerf Van der Giessen-de Noord N.V.

http://data.europeana.eu/item/2021648/re.description: Tijdschrift "SPORTRMEDIZIN UND OLYMPISCHE SPIELE 1936". Een eenmalig"Festschrift der Sportärzteschaft" van de sportartsen van het "Deutsche Medizinische Wochenschrift", uitgebracht t.g.v. de IVde Olympische Winterspelen in Garmisch-Partenkirchen in 1936. Het tijdschrift heeft 44 pagina's met op de voorkant een aquarel met sneeuw en bergen, gemaakt door A.v.Scanzoni. Het bevat verslagen van het "Internationale Sportärtztekongress", gehouden van 27-31 juli 1936, voorafgaand aan de spelen en bevat artikelen over sportmedisch onderzoek m.b.t. wintersport, zoals skiblessures, lawines, fysiologisch onderzoek van o.a. het hart bij langlaufen, longaandoeningen, stofwisseling, sporttraining in het hooggebergte, klimaatonderzoek en wintersport. Onder de vele internationale gedelegeerden waren Prof. Dr. F.J.J. Buytendijk, van het Fysiologisch Instituut te Groningen en Dr. med. J.H.O. Reijs uit Den Haag. Olympische Winterspelenspelen Garmisch- Partenkirchen 1936.

http://data.europeana.eu/item/2022703/pa.description: Lucerna realizada en cerámica común con pasta grisácea. Posee el disco redondeado y pica decorada con volutas dobles. Tiene el margo liso y semicaído hacia fuera, separado del disco por dos molduras, el asa tipo lazo y la base anular. La decoración moldeada en el disco representa a dos gladiadores enfrentados. El de la izquierda, a derecha, arrodillado y vencido, mira a su contrincante, que está a izquierda, y parece sujetarlo con su brazo derecho y apuntarlo con su espada corta, sujetada en su mano derecha. Ambos llevan el mismo tipo de vestimenta, consistente en un caso con penacho, torso desnudo, subligaculum y balteus. Completan el vestuario la manica en el brazo derecho y las grebas en las piernas.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/2022703/pa.title: Lucerna

http://data.europeana.eu/item/2022703/pa.description: Ambas caras del vaso están decoradas con escenas deportivas, dos luchadores en pleno combate. En la cara A, dos luchadores, desnudos, de cuerpors robustos y con el cabello corto están representados practicando una llave dentro de la orthopalé (combate erguido). Uno de ellos, agachado, sujeta a su contrincante por los omoplatos intentando así destabilizarle para lanzarle al suelo. Su rival contiene el ataque sujetando al segundo luchador por el hombro. La tensión de la llave se indica mediante incisiones a la altura del vientre, muslos y rodillas. En la cara B, una escena similar, de menor ejecución técnica, en la que la llave se practica a la altura de los glúteos. Las escenas aparecen enmarcadas por grandes palmetas que nacen en la parte inferior de las asas. El interior de la copa está decorado con círculo en reserva y sucesión de círculos inscritos en barniz negro y nuevamente. Esta disciplina se introduce en los Juegos Olímpicos en la 18ª Olimpíada (708 a.C.) tanto como prueba independiente o integrada en el pentatlón. Era una de las disciplinas más apreciadas de las competiciones deportivas, lo que hace que Platón en sus Leyes (7-795e y 796a.) sitúe a la lucha en un primer plano para la práctica del deporte. Se distinguían dos fases en el combate: la orthopalè (combate erguido) y la katô palè (combate en el suelo). La lucha se  caracterizaba por la utilización de toda una serie de llaves que recibían su nombre de las diferentes partes del cuerpo en las que se aplicaban. En la lucha resultaba fundamental el buen apoyo de los pies para evitar ser desestabilizado por el contrincante en la primera acometida. Por eso los luchadores se apoyaban sobre la base de los dedos de los pies con al menos una de las rodillas flexionadas, como observamos en una de las imágenes de este vaso. Se alzaba con la victoria aquél que lanzaba a su adversario al suelo en tres ocasiones haciéndole tocar los hombros con el suelo.
http://data.europeana.eu/item/2022703/pa.title: Copa

http://data.europeana.eu/item/91643/SMVK.description: Kroppen på den här cittran är gjord av en urholkad bit kejsarträ, vilket är det mest populära träslaget på cittror i Östasien. Var och en av de tolv silkessträngarna sitter på en A-formad brygga. Silkessträngarnas extra längd är surrade i ena änden och fästa vid snören som håller strängarna sträckta tack vare en elaborerad knut längst ut på instrumentet. Enligt De tre kungarikenas historia (Samguksagi) kommer gayageum-cittran från början från Gaya, och är inspirerad av kinesiska cittror. Instrumentet har sedan utvecklats till flera olika sorters cittror som finns i Korea idag.
